ftbuniversity.ic2chap.title=Industrial Craft 2

ftbuniversity.ic2wrench.title=You're Welcome
ftbuniversity.ic2wrench.subtitle=制作一个 Wrench
ftbuniversity.ic2wrench.desc1=Normally, IC2 machines have to be right-clicked with an IC2 &bWrench&r to be &6picked up quickly&r. Even worse, &6mining them up with a pickaxe would give back a Machine Casing&r instead of the machine itself.
ftbuniversity.ic2wrench.desc2=&nHowever&r, &cthat sucks&r, so &6we disabled it&r. Use whatever the heck you want. Wrenches are still faster, though.
ftbuniversity.ic2wrench.desc3=You're welcome.
ftbuniversity.ic2wrench.task=Any IC2 Wrench

ftbuniversity.treetap.title=O' Rubber Tree, O' Rubber Tree
ftbuniversity.treetap.subtitle=制作一个 Treetap
ftbuniversity.treetap.desc1=The &bTreetap&r is probably the first tool from IC2 that you'll be making.
ftbuniversity.treetap.desc2=&6Find a Rubber Tree&r somewhere in the world. On one of the logs, you'll likely find some exposed sap. &6Use the Treetap on a sap hole&r to extract some &bSticky Resin&r.
ftbuniversity.treetap.desc3=If you only harvest it once, the Sticky Resin &6will eventually regenerate&r. You can harvesting an emptied sap hole to get more, though that &chas a chance of permanently draining it&r.

ftbuniversity.ic2tools.title=HM06 HM01
ftbuniversity.ic2tools.subtitle=制作一个 Forge Hammer and Cutters
ftbuniversity.ic2tools.desc1=The &bForge Hammer&r can be used to &6craft Plates&r and, slightly less importantly, Item Casings.
ftbuniversity.ic2tools.desc2=The &bCutter&r can be used to &6craft Cables&r, which carry EU.
ftbuniversity.ic2tools.desc3=Both tools use up durability when used.
ftbuniversity.ic2tools.rewards=IC2 Unbreaking II Tools

ftbuniversity.ironfurnace.title=Efficient Smelting
ftbuniversity.ironfurnace.subtitle=制作一个 Iron Furnace
ftbuniversity.ironfurnace.desc=The &bIron Furnace&r is &625%% more efficient&r at smelting items; that is, fuels that would normally smelt 8 items instead smelt 10.

ftbuniversity.ic2generator.subtitle=制作一个 Generator
ftbuniversity.ic2generator.desc1=The &bGenerator&r will generate EU from furnace fuel. It &6generates 500 EU per item that fuel would smelt&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2generator.desc2=You can charge items by inserting them into the top slot.
ftbuniversity.ic2generator.desc3=The Generator is power tier 1: LV. See the next quest for more information.

ftbuniversity.ic2solar.title=Praise the Sun
ftbuniversity.ic2solar.subtitle=制作一个 Solar Panel
ftbuniversity.ic2solar.desc1=A &bSolar Panel&r &6generates 1 EU/t&r and outputs at &6Low Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2solar.desc2=They are best used in groups.

ftbuniversity.compactsolars.title=Compact Solars
ftbuniversity.compactsolars.subtitle=制作一个 higher-voltage Solar Panel
ftbuniversity.compactsolars.desc1=The addon &eCompact Solars&r adds more powerful Solar Panels for each voltage.
ftbuniversity.compactsolars.desc2=The &bLow Voltage Solar Array&r generates 32 EU/t at LV.
ftbuniversity.compactsolars.desc3=The &bMedium Voltage Solar Array&r generates 64 EU/t at MV.
ftbuniversity.compactsolars.desc4=The &bHigh Voltage Solar Array&r generates 512 EU/t at HV.

ftbuniversity.ic2geotherm.subtitle=制作一个 Geothermal Generator
ftbuniversity.ic2geotherm.desc1=The &bGeothermal Generator&r will &6generate 20 EU/t&r when it has Lava. A single bucket will produce &610,000 EU total&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2geotherm.desc2=Power is output at &6Low Voltage&r.

ftbuniversity.teacheu.title=You're Not Dealing With the Average Energy Unit
ftbuniversity.teacheu.subtitle=Learn about EU
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc1=&bEU&r (Energy Units) act fairly different than RF.
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc2=EU is not only transferred per tick, unlike most other mods. Instead, it uses &6packets&r. Multiple packets can be sent per tick. EU per packet is the &6voltage&r, EU per tick is the &6current&r.
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc3=There are &65 voltage tiers&r. The tiers are:
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc4=• Low Voltage: 31 EU/p and lower
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc5=• Medium Voltage: 32-511 EU/p
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc6=• High Voltage: 512-2047 EU/p
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc7=• Extreme Voltage: 2048-8191 EU/p
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc8=• Insane Voltage: 8192 EU/p and higher
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc9=If a machine gets too high a voltage, &cit will explode&r. If a Cable tries to carry too high a voltage, &cit will burn up&r. Remember, voltage is &nnot&r EU/t.
ftbuniversity.teacheu.desc10=Machines and Cables will show their &6Power Tier in their tooltip&r.

ftbuniversity.transformupgrade.subtitle=制作一个 Transformer Upgrade
ftbuniversity.transformupgrade.desc1=Installing a &bTransformer Upgrade&r onto a machine to &6allow it to accept higher voltage&r without exploding.
ftbuniversity.transformupgrade.desc2=The more you install, the higher voltage it can accept.

ftbuniversity.tincables.title=Danger, Danger! Low Voltage!
ftbuniversity.tincables.subtitle=Make Tin Cables
ftbuniversity.tincables.desc1=&bTin Cables&r can &6transfer LV power&r.
ftbuniversity.tincables.desc2=Touching powered &6uninsulated Cables will shock you&r, dealing damage. &6Insulated Cables are safe to touch.&r
ftbuniversity.tincables.task=Tin Cables

ftbuniversity.ic2loss.title=&m:.|:;&r
ftbuniversity.ic2loss.subtitle=Learn about energy loss
ftbuniversity.ic2loss.desc1=All Cables have &bloss&r; some energy is lost every block it travels.
ftbuniversity.ic2loss.desc2=Oddly, higher tier cables actually have &ohigher&r energy loss per block. However, the amount removed is &6per packet&r, so it is &6better to have higher packet sizes&r, so higher voltages perform better.
ftbuniversity.ic2loss.desc3=The exception is &6Glass Fibre Cables&r, which have the lowest but are the most expensive.

ftbuniversity.ic2loud.title=Mawp
ftbuniversity.ic2loud.subtitle=IC2 be loud
ftbuniversity.ic2loud.desc1=Most IC2 machines make noise as they work. Really loud noise. Like, a lot.
ftbuniversity.ic2loud.desc2=In the &6Music & Sounds&r settings, there's a new slider for IC2 machines. You can turn that down if you don't want your ears to be assaulted every time you use a machine.

ftbuniversity.ic2furnace.title=Microwave
ftbuniversity.ic2furnace.subtitle=制作一个 Electric Furnace
ftbuniversity.ic2furnace.desc1=The &bElectric Furnace&r is slightly faster than a normal furnace, and is &6powered by LV EU&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2furnace.desc2=Most IC2 machines can have Upgrades installed. You can see installable upgrades in the &9[i]&r in the top left.

ftbuniversity.macerator.title=Ore Doubling
ftbuniversity.macerator.subtitle=制作一个 Macerator
ftbuniversity.macerator.desc=The &bMacerator&r crushes items using &6LV EU&r. Its main draw is that it can &6double ores&r.
ftbuniversity.macerator.rewards=Ores

ftbuniversity.extractor.subtitle=制作一个 Extractor
ftbuniversity.extractor.desc1=The &bExtractor&r uses &6LV EU&r to extract items from other items.
ftbuniversity.extractor.desc2=Its biggest selling point is the ability to &6get more Rubber&r out of Sticky Resin and Rubber Saplings and Logs.

ftbuniversity.batbox.title=May Contain Bats
ftbuniversity.batbox.subtitle=制作一个 BatBox
ftbuniversity.batbox.desc1=The &bBatBox&r can &6store up to 40,000 EU&r. Power is output through the side with a dot, and can be input from any other side.
ftbuniversity.batbox.desc2=The BatBox can only input &6LV EU&r, and outputs the same.
ftbuniversity.batbox.desc3=You can &6charge and discharge&r items in the GUI. Putting Redstone in the bottom slot will generate 800 EU.
ftbuniversity.batbox.desc4=You can also set it to emit a redstone signal when full, partially full, or empty.

ftbuniversity.orewashingplant.title=Ore 2-and-4/9ths-ing
ftbuniversity.orewashingplant.subtitle=制作一个 Ore Washing Plant
ftbuniversity.orewashingplant.desc1=The &bOre Washing Plant&r can &6further increase your ore yield&r (using &6LV EU&r).
ftbuniversity.orewashingplant.desc2=Using 1,000mB of Water, it will wash Crushed Ore into Purified Crushed Ore, &6as well as 2 Tiny Piles of Dust&r (and some Stone Dust).

ftbuniversity.ic2pump.title=Pump It Up!
ftbuniversity.ic2pump.subtitle=制作一个 Pump
ftbuniversity.ic2pump.desc1=The &bPump&r uses &6LV EU&r to pick up fluids that it's facing (on the grate side, rotate with a Wrench).
ftbuniversity.ic2pump.desc2=It does will also pump fluids adjacent to the block it's facing. If you want it to pump &6infinite water&r, it must be a &65x5&r pool.

ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.title=Sewer Level
ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.subtitle=Make IC2 Pipes
ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.desc1=&bPipes&r can carry and transfer fluids over a distance. They do not connect to adjacent blocks automatically, unless placed on them.
ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.desc2=There are &62 types^r of Pipes, each come in &64 sizes&r. Bigger/higher-tier Pipes &6simply move fluids faster&r. You can safely connect two Pipes of different types and sizes.
ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.desc3=You can manually set connections using the &bWrench (New)&r. Why &nonly&r the Wrench (New)? Who knows!
ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.desc4=Hold it in your hand to see all connection sides, then click on the connection you want to force.
ftbuniversity.ic2pipes.task=Any Pipe

ftbuniversity.pumpattach.title=Slurp
ftbuniversity.pumpattach.subtitle=制作一个 Pump Attachment
ftbuniversity.pumpattach.desc1=&bPump Attachments&r are applied to Pipes to allow them to pull fluids out of the block they're facing.
ftbuniversity.pumpattach.desc2=Despite their names, they &6do not use EU&r. The "MV" one simply pulls more fluid per tick.
ftbuniversity.pumpattach.desc3=They &6cannot be turned off&r.
ftbuniversity.pumpattach.desc4=The &bAttachment Remover&r can be used to remove them from Pipes.
ftbuniversity.pumpattach.task=Either Pump Attachment

ftbuniversity.solidcanning.title=School Lunch
ftbuniversity.solidcanning.subtitle=制作一个 Solid Canning Machine
ftbuniversity.solidcanning.desc1=The &bSolid Canning Machine&r uses &6LV EU&r to &6fill Tin Cans&r.
ftbuniversity.solidcanning.desc2=This is used to create Fuel Rods for Nuclear Reactors, as well as making &6(Filled) Tin Cans&r. Each gives only 2 points of food, but clicking a stack will eat all of them at once, up to the point where you're full.

ftbuniversity.fluidcanning.title=/
ftbuniversity.fluidcanning.subtitle=制作一个 Fluid/Solid Canning Machine
ftbuniversity.fluidcanning.desc1=The &bFluid/Solid Canning Machine&r can do everything the Solid Canning Machine can, but also has some fluid recipes, and can fill/empty fluid containers.
ftbuniversity.fluidcanning.desc2=Click the button at the left to switch between &6Canning&r, &6Drain from Cell into Tank&r, &6Fill Cell from Tank&r, and &6Fluid Enrich (Tank or Cell)&r modes.
ftbuniversity.fluidcanning.desc3=There are two tanks in the machine, and a button to swap the contents of each.
ftbuniversity.fluidcanning.desc4=Click on the progress bar to see each modes' recipes.

ftbuniversity.ic2jetpack.subtitle=制作一个 Jetpack
ftbuniversity.ic2jetpack.desc1=The &bJetpack&r lets you quickly fly upwards by holding space.
ftbuniversity.ic2jetpack.desc2=It does not use EU, it &6uses Biogas&r instead.
ftbuniversity.ic2jetpack.desc3=The Jetpack cannot fly over y=245.

ftbuniversity.ic2elecjet.subtitle=制作一个 Electric Jetpack
ftbuniversity.ic2elecjet.desc1=The &bElectric Jetpack&r lets you fly upwards by holding space, and is powered by EU.
ftbuniversity.ic2elecjet.desc2=The Electric Jetpack cannot fly over y=185.

ftbuniversity.ic2jetpackmodes=The "Mode Switch Key" keybind (see controls menu) will toggle &6Hover Mode&r, which constantly uses a small amount of fuel to make you hover.

ftbuniversity.jetpackattachplate.title=That Thing That's In Every Chestplate Recipe
ftbuniversity.jetpackattachplate.subtitle=制作一个 Jetpack Attachment Plate
ftbuniversity.jetpackattachplate.desc1=The &bJetpack Attachment Plate&r can be &6crafted with any Chestplate&r and an Electric Jetpack, and it will &6make that Chestplate function like one&r.
ftbuniversity.jetpackattachplate.desc2=You can attach a Jetpack to literally everything that can fit in the chestplate slot, including Elytras, BatPacks, and Backpacks.

ftbuniversity.metalformer.title=The Metal Formerly Known as Ingot
ftbuniversity.metalformer.subtitle=制作一个 Metal Former
ftbuniversity.metalformer.desc1=The &bMetal Former&r uses &6LV EU&r to essentially replace the Forge Hammer and Cutter.
ftbuniversity.metalformer.desc2=It has three modes: &6Extruding&r, &6Rolling&r, and &6Cutting&r.
ftbuniversity.metalformer.desc3=• Extruding makes cylindrical items, like &6Cables&r.
ftbuniversity.metalformer.desc4=• Rolling makes flat items, like &6Plates&r.
ftbuniversity.metalformer.desc5=• Cutting cuts items, like &6Plates into Cables&r (which is more efficient but tedious).

ftbuniversity.magnetizer.title=Goin' &oUuuuuuup!&r
ftbuniversity.magnetizer.subtitle=制作一个 Magnetizer
ftbuniversity.magnetizer.desc1=When supplied with &6LV EU&r, the &bMagnetizer&r will magnetize adjacent Iron Fences.
ftbuniversity.magnetizer.desc2=If a player wearing any metal boots touches magnetized Iron Fences, they will be flung upwards at great speed. Sneaking players are unaffected.
ftbuniversity.magnetizer.desc3=The Magnetizer will only magnetize up to 20 Iron Fences above and below itself.
ftbuniversity.magnetizer.desc4=This works great as a way to quickly move between floors of your base!

ftbuniversity.ic2compressor.title=Squ&oeeeeeze&r
ftbuniversity.ic2compressor.subtitle=制作一个 Compressor
ftbuniversity.ic2compressor.desc=The &bCompressor&r uses &6LV EU&r to compress items into other items.

ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.title=Hot Stuff, Coming Through
ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.subtitle=Learn about heat
ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.desc1=&bHeat&r is another energy system added by IC2.
ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.desc2=Heat is &6generated&r in certain machines (directly above this quest), and &6used&r by certain others (directly below).
ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.desc3=There are &6no wires that carry heat&r; the heat generator must be placed &6directly adjacent&r to the heat user.
ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.desc4=Heat is &6transferred through the orange face&r of the machine. To work, the orange faces of both the generator and user &6must be touching&r.
ftbuniversity.teachic2heat.desc5=Heat is measured in &6hU&r: Heat Units.

ftbuniversity.solidfuelfire.subtitle=制作一个 Solid Fuel Firebox
ftbuniversity.solidfuelfire.desc1=The &bSolid Fuel Firebox&r will generate hU using &6furnace fuels&r.
ftbuniversity.solidfuelfire.desc2=It has a small chance of producing Ashes as a byproduct.

ftbuniversity.electricheater.title=Electri Cheater
ftbuniversity.electricheater.subtitle=制作一个 Electric Heater
ftbuniversity.electricheater.desc1=The &bElectric Heater&r accepts up to &6EV EU&r to &6produce hU&r.
ftbuniversity.electricheater.desc2=To work, you must insert &6up to 10 Coils&r. Each Coil increases the hU output by 10, and increases the EU requirement by 10.

ftbuniversity.liquidfuelfire.subtitle=制作一个 Liquid Fuel Firebox
ftbuniversity.liquidfuelfire.desc=The &bLiquid Fuel Firebox&r generates &6hU using Forestry's Biomass&r (but not IC2's, strangely), &6Forestry's Ethanol&r, and &6IC2's Biogas&r.

ftbuniversity.ic2stirling.subtitle=制作一个 Stirling Generator
ftbuniversity.ic2stirling.desc=The &bSterling Generator&r produces &61 EU for every 2 hU&r it is given.

ftbuniversity.ic2blastfurnace.subtitle=制作一个 Blast Furnace
ftbuniversity.ic2blastfurnace.desc1=The &bBlast Furnace&r uses &6hU and Air&r to make &6Steel&r using Iron, also producing Slag as a byproduct.
ftbuniversity.ic2blastfurnace.desc2=Get the Air by &6compressing empty Universal Fluid Cells&r, and then insert them into the bottom left slot.

ftbuniversity.ic2crops.title=What's an Agricraft?
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.subtitle=Make Crops
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc1=&bCrops&r can be placed on Farmland to allow the crossbreeding of crops. You can use any vanilla non-tree plants (seeds, flowers, canes, etc).
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc2=Crossbreeding two of the same crop has a chance to mutate them, increasing either their &6Growth&r, &6Gain&r, and &6Resistance&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc3=• Growth and Gain are how fast they grow, and how much they drop.
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc4=• Resistance is specifically &6resistance &oto weeds&r. More on that in the next quest.
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc5=Placing a &6single&r Crop stick will allow you to plant seeds on them. Placing Crop sticks &6twice on the same block&r will allow it to crossbreed two adjacent blocks' crops, if they are on Crop Sticks.
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc6=Plant the seeds on the outer Crop sticks and allow them to grow, and eventually they might spread to adjacent Crop sticks.
ftbuniversity.ic2crops.desc7=Crops that have modified traits will drop &6seed bags&r when broken, instead of regular seeds.

ftbuniversity.ic2weed.title=The Weed Quest
ftbuniversity.ic2weed.subtitle=制作一个 Weeding Trowel
ftbuniversity.ic2weed.desc1=If you leave Crop sticks empty for too long, they will eventually be overrun with &6Weeds&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2weed.desc2=Weeds will &6spread&r to adjacent Crop sticks, &cdestroying whatever crop was already there&r. It should be fairly obvious why this is a bad thing.
ftbuniversity.ic2weed.desc3=You can use a &bWeeding Trowel&r on weeds to clear the Weeds from the Crop sticks, giving them to you as an item.
ftbuniversity.ic2weed.desc4=You can also use a &bUniversal Fluid Cell full of Weed-Ex&r on Crop sticks to protect them from Weeds. However, &6this can lower the crop's stats&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2weed.desc5=Fully grown Weeds have a chance of growing Grass around it, which could theoretically be a source of Wheat if you don't have any.

ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.title=I Was Elected to Breed, Not to Read
ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.subtitle=制作一个 Cropnalyzer
ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.desc1=The &bCropnalyzer&r uses EU to scan seed bags to tell you information about them. It takes 4 scans to get all their information.
ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.desc2=• The first scan will simply show you &6what crop it produces&r.
ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.desc3=• The second scan will show you &6its tier&r (1-8), and who discovered it (ie, who made the mod it came from).
ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.desc4=• The third scan will show some &6keywords&r, like its color, what type of crop it is, etc.
ftbuniversity.cropnalyzer.desc5=• The fourth and final scan will show the &6Growth, Gain, and Resistance&r of the seed bag.

ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.title=SEEDS?! DUNCAN!
ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.subtitle=Learn how to get new crops
ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.desc1=Somewhat counterintuitively, you do not get new crop species based on specific combinations of other species.
ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.desc2=Instead, you have to &6combine two seeds with keywords similar to the target crop&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.desc3=It is possible for two of the same crop to crossbreed into a different one.
ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.desc4=The tier of crop you get is usually within the range of the two other crops, give or take one.
ftbuniversity.ic2seeds.task=Any seed bag

ftbuniversity.ic2recycler.title=This Machine Creates Potato Knishes
ftbuniversity.ic2recycler.subtitle=制作一个 Recycler
ftbuniversity.ic2recycler.desc1=Using &6LV EU&r, the &bRecycler&r will destroy any item given to it, with a 12.5%% chance of &6producing Scrap&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2recycler.desc2=Scrap can be burned as fuel, crafted into Scrap Boxes (which can be used to give a random item), and, most importantly, &6speeding up the Mass Fabricator&r.

ftbuniversity.ic2energyup.title=Energy Go Up
ftbuniversity.ic2energyup.subtitle=制作一个 Energy Storage Upgrade
ftbuniversity.ic2energyup.desc1=For each &bEnergy Storage Upgrade&r installed into a machine, it can &6store 10,000 more EU&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2energyup.desc2=You can install 4 stacks onto a machine to allow it to store &n2,561,200&r EU. I mean, not that you would. You totally can though.

ftbuniversity.ic2overclock.title=I Have a Legal Obligation to Accelerate
ftbuniversity.ic2overclock.subtitle=制作一个 Overclocker Upgrade
ftbuniversity.ic2overclock.desc1=&bOverclocker Upgrades&r can be installed onto machines to make them work faster, using more EU.
ftbuniversity.ic2overclock.desc2=Each Overclocker Upgrade installs &6reduces the time required to 70%%&r current (multiplicatively, so 2 would reduce it to 100*0.7*0.7=34.3%%), but also makes it &6require 60%% more power&r (again, multiplicatively).
ftbuniversity.ic2overclock.desc3=You can hover over a slot with multiple Overclocker Upgrades, and the tooltip will say the cumulative effect they have.

ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.title=Items Come In, Items Go Out, You Can't Explain That
ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.subtitle=Make Ejector/Pulling Upgrades
ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.desc1=&bEjector Upgrades&r can be installed onto a machine to make it automatically push out items/fluids in the output slot to an adjacent block.
ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.desc2=&bPulling Upgrades&r do the same, except they pull items/fluids into the input slot from an adjacent block.
ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.desc3=By default, they will push/pull into/from a random valid side. You can right-click the Upgrade onto the face of any block, and the Upgrade will only try to use that side (click the top face to make it use the top face, etc).
ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.task1=Ejector Upgrades
ftbuniversity.ic2moveups.task2=Pulling Upgrades

ftbuniversity.ic2mv.title=Medium Voltage
ftbuniversity.ic2mv.subtitle=Make MV Cables
ftbuniversity.ic2mv.desc1=&bCopper Cables&r can transfer &6Medium Voltage&r EU. The tooltip says it transfers 128 EU/t, but it's actually &6128 EU/p&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2mv.desc2=&6Higher voltage machines can accept lower voltage inputs.&r That means you can pass LV current through MV cables and into MV machines.
ftbuniversity.ic2mv.task=Copper Cables

ftbuniversity.inductionfurnace.title=Macrowave
ftbuniversity.inductionfurnace.subtitle=制作一个 Induction Furnace
ftbuniversity.inductionfurnace.desc1=The &bInduction Furnace&r uses &6MV EU&r to slowly build up heat, smelting items. &6The higher the heat, the faster it smelts.&r
ftbuniversity.inductionfurnace.desc2=You can apply a redstone signal to keep building heat even when not in use, though this will make it constantly drain EU.
ftbuniversity.inductionfurnace.desc3=Additionally, the Induction Furnace has &62 input and output slots&r, so you can smelt two items at once.

ftbuniversity.ic2packs.title=Power Packs
ftbuniversity.ic2packs.subtitle=制作一个 energy-storing backpack
ftbuniversity.ic2packs.desc1=The &bBatPack&r, &6Advanced Batpack&r, and &bEnergypack&r, when worn in the chestplate slot, will allow electric items in your inventory to use its charge.
ftbuniversity.ic2packs.desc2=Higher tiers store more EU, and can charge higher-tier items.
ftbuniversity.ic2packs.task=Any energy-storing pack

ftbuniversity.ic2solarhelm.title=Thinking Cap
ftbuniversity.ic2solarhelm.subtitle=制作一个 Solar Helmet
ftbuniversity.ic2solarhelm.desc=The &bSolar Helmet&r, when worn and in the sun, will charge your Batpack at 1 EU/t.

ftbuniversity.ic2staticshoes.title=Shuffle Dynamism
ftbuniversity.ic2staticshoes.subtitle=Make Static Shoes
ftbuniversity.ic2staticshoes.desc=&bStatic Shoes&r, while worn, charge your Batpack 1 EU for every 5 blocks walked.

ftbuniversity.ic2miscpowered.title=Electric Tools
ftbuniversity.ic2miscpowered.subtitle=制作一个 electric tool
ftbuniversity.ic2miscpowered.desc=The &bElectric Wrench&r, &bElectric Treetap&r, and &bElectric Hoe&r are simply tools that use EU instead of durability.
ftbuniversity.ic2miscpowered.task=Any electric tool

# Yes, I made this its own quest to 制作一个 DOOM reference
ftbuniversity.chainsaw.title=Rip and Tear
ftbuniversity.chainsaw.subtitle=制作一个 Chainsaw
ftbuniversity.chainsaw.desc=The &bChainsaw&r uses EU to chop wood, shear sheep, and damage mobs.

ftbuniversity.ic2drill1.title=WRRRRRR
ftbuniversity.ic2drill1.subtitle=制作一个 Mining Drill
ftbuniversity.ic2drill1.desc1=The &bMining Drill&r is essentially an EU-powered iron-level pickaxe.
ftbuniversity.ic2drill1.desc2=It can be upgraded into the &bDiamond Mining Drill&r which, as the name would suggest, can mine anything a Diamond Pickaxe can. It is also faster.
ftbuniversity.ic2drill1.task=Either Mining Drill

ftbuniversity.ic2miner.title=Quarry, Kinda
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.subtitle=制作一个 Miner
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.desc1=The &bMiner&r will dig a tunnel straight down, putting all block drops into its internal inventory.
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.desc2=To run, it needs a &6Drill&r below Iridium tier and some &bMining Pipes&r. Each block in the tunnel uses up one Mining Pipe. It also obviously requires &6LV EU&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.desc3=If the Drill is removed, the Mining Pipes will retract.
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.desc4=Optionally, you can insert an &6OD or OV Scanner&r, which will allow it to mine ores that are near the bottom Mining Pipe, instead of only directly below.
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.desc5=The OD Scanner will give it a &67x7&r area, and the OV will give a &613x13&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2miner.desc6=Additionally, having a Pump adjacent to it will allow it to pick up fluids.

ftbuniversity.cfpowder.title=Construction Foam
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.subtitle=Get Construction Foam set up
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc1=&bConstruction Foam&r is sprayed in the world until it hardens.
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc2=Construction Foam fluid is made in the &6Fluid/Solid Canning Machine&r, and then from there inserted into a &bCF Sprayer&r.
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc3=Spraying it directly will just 制作一个 random shapeless glob. If you spray it on &6Scaffolds&r though, it will take their shape.
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc4=Spraying on &6Iron Scaffolds&r will create &6Reinforced Stone&r, which is &6highly resistant to nuclear explosions&r. Two layers will completely nullify a nuclear meltdown.
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc5=Spraying on anything else will create &6Construction Foam Walls&r which are also fairly resistant, though not nearly as much.
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc6=Wearing a full &bCF Backpack&r will allow feed the CF Sprayer, much like a BatPack.
ftbuniversity.cfpowder.desc7=Additionally, &6you can cover Cables with Construction Foam&r and they will still function.

ftbuniversity.ic2paint.title=The Joy of Painting
ftbuniversity.ic2paint.subtitle=制作一个 Painter
ftbuniversity.ic2paint.desc=The &bPainter&r can be crafted with any dye, and then it will &6color Construction Foam Walls&r when used on them.

ftbuniversity.obscurator.subtitle=制作一个 Obscurator
ftbuniversity.obscurator.desc1=The &bOscurator&r allows you to retexture every face of a Construction Foam Wall to the texture of another block.
ftbuniversity.obscurator.desc2=To set a texture, &6sneak right-click it on a block&r to grab that face's texture, then right-click on the CF Wall to set it.

ftbuniversity.thermalcentrifuge.title=Hot Spinny Thing
ftbuniversity.thermalcentrifuge.subtitle=制作一个 Thermal Centrifuge
ftbuniversity.thermalcentrifuge.desc1=The &bThermal Centrifuge&r is the final step of IC2's ore processing (it uses &6MV EU&r).
ftbuniversity.thermalcentrifuge.desc2=Putting in some Purified Crushed Ore will make Pulverized Dust, as well as giving an &6additional Tiny Pile of Dust of a similar ore&r (Tin gives Iron, etc).
ftbuniversity.thermalcentrifuge.desc3=It also has some miscellaneous other recipes, see JEI.
ftbuniversity.thermalcentrifuge.desc4=It builds up speed as it gains heat. You can give it a redstone signal to make it heat up when not in use.

ftbuniversity.cesu.title=Chemical Electrical Storage Unit
ftbuniversity.cesu.subtitle=制作一个 CESU
ftbuniversity.cesu.desc1=The &bCESU&r can store up to &6300,000 EU&r, and outputs at &6Medium Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.cesu.desc2=Like the BatBox, power is &6output through the face that looks different&r, and input through any other.

ftbuniversity.ic2tesla.title=Nikola
ftbuniversity.ic2tesla.subtitle=制作一个 Tesla Coil
ftbuniversity.ic2tesla.desc1=Using a decent chunk of &6MV EU&r, the Tesla Coil will deal &6massive damage&r to all entities within a &69x9x9&r area surrounding it.
ftbuniversity.ic2tesla.desc2=The Tesla Coil only works when &6given a redstone signal&r. You should probably make it so it can be turned off from a distance.
ftbuniversity.ic2tesla.desc3=The amount of damage it deals depends on the amount of EU/p it gets, though it still can only accept up to MV.

ftbuniversity.lvtrans.title=LV↔MV
ftbuniversity.lvtrans.subtitle=制作一个 LV-Transformer
ftbuniversity.lvtrans.desc1=The &bLV-Transformer&r will allow you to &6convert between Low and Medium Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.lvtrans.desc2=The side that has a different texture is the higher-voltage side, and all others are the lower-voltage sides.
ftbuniversity.lvtrans.desc3=There are two modes: &6Step-Down&r and &6Step-Up&r.
ftbuniversity.lvtrans.desc4=In Step-Down mode, it will accept energy from the higher-voltage side, and then send energy out of the lower-voltage sides. Vice versa for Step-Up.
ftbuniversity.lvtrans.desc5=Using a Wrench (New), you can point where the higher-voltage side is facing.

ftbuniversity.ic2hv.title=High Voltage
ftbuniversity.ic2hv.subtitle=Make HV Cables (no not those)
ftbuniversity.ic2hv.desc1=&bGold Cables&r can transfer up to &6High Voltage&r, carrying &6512 EU/p&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2hv.desc2=Due to the high amount of current they can carry, &6only the 2x Insulted Gold Cable will fully protect from shocks&r when EU is flowing through.
ftbuniversity.ic2hv.desc3=Oddly, the item &ocalled&r "HV Cable" is &cnot high voltage&r, it's extreme voltage.
ftbuniversity.ic2hv.task=Gold Cables

ftbuniversity.ic2teleporter.title=Older Than Ender Pearls
ftbuniversity.ic2teleporter.subtitle=制作一个 Teleporter
ftbuniversity.ic2teleporter.desc1=When a &bTeleporter&r is given a redstone signal, it will teleport any entity on top of it to the linked Teleporter.
ftbuniversity.ic2teleporter.desc2=Link two Teleporters by using a &6Frequency Transmitter&r on both of them.
ftbuniversity.ic2teleporter.desc3=Cables do not connect to the Teleporter. Instead, you have to put an EU-storing machine (like the BatBox or MFE) directly adjacent and aimed at it.
ftbuniversity.ic2teleporter.desc4=The EU cost depends on the mass and distance being teleported. So a player with a full inventory teleporting thousands of blocks would require more EU.

ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.title=Wazer Wifle
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.subtitle=Make the Mining Laser
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc1=The &bMining Laser&r uses EU to &6shoot a laser beam that mines blocks&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc2=It has &67 modes&r, which you can cycle through by holding the &6Mode Switch Key&r (see controls) and right-clicking.
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc3=• &6Mining&r: average everything
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc4=• &6Low-focus&r: very short range, low damage and power
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc5=• &6Long-range&r: high range, damage, and power
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc6=• &6Scatter&r: shoots 25 average-power beams that spread out
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc7=• &6Explosive&r: beam explodes when it reaches a block
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc8=• &6Horizontal&r: Identical to mining mode, but only moves horizontally
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc9=• &6Super-heat&r: Smelts blocks mined
ftbuniversity.ic2mininglaser.desc10=• &63x3&r: shoots 9 average-power beams that stay parallel

ftbuniversity.mfe.title=Multi-Functional Electric storage unit
ftbuniversity.mfe.subtitle=制作一个 MFE
ftbuniversity.mfe.desc1=The &bMFE&r can store up to &64,000,000 EU&r, and outputs at &6High Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.mfe.desc2=Hopefully by now you understand what sides are input and output.

ftbuniversity.mfsuupgrade.subtitle=制作一个 MFSU Upgrade Kit
ftbuniversity.mfsuupgrade.desc1=The &bMFSU Upgrade Kit&r can be used on an MFE to turn it into an MFSU, keeping its EU.
ftbuniversity.mfsuupgrade.desc2=Why one of these doesn't exist for every tier, we'll never know.

ftbuniversity.mvtrans.title=MV↔HV
ftbuniversity.mvtrans.subtitle=制作一个 HV-Transformer
ftbuniversity.mvtrans.desc1=The &bMV-Transformer&r will allow you to &6convert between Medium and High Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.mvtrans.desc2=All other functionality is identical to the LV-Transformer. See its quest for details.

ftbuniversity.ic2advancedminer.subtitle=制作一个 Advanced Miner
ftbuniversity.ic2advancedminer.desc1=The &bAdvanced Miner&r &6does not require a Mining Drill or Mining Pipes&r, and instead uses only &6HV EU&r and a &6Scanner&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2advancedminer.desc2=In its GUI, you can set a whitelist/blacklist and if it should use Silk Touch (which increases EU cost).
ftbuniversity.ic2advancedminer.desc3=When running, it will say the relative coordinates of the block it is currently scanning.
ftbuniversity.ic2advancedminer.desc4=You must place an inventory adjacent to the Advanced Miner to collect drops.

ftbuniversity.matfab.title=MyMatFab
ftbuniversity.matfab.subtitle=制作一个 Matter Fabricator
ftbuniversity.matfab.desc1=The &bMatter Fabricator&r uses a massive amount of &6HV EU&r to generate &6UU-Matter&r. Specifically, it takes &61,000,000 EU&r per mB of UU-Matter unupgraded.
ftbuniversity.matfab.desc2=However, you can &6supply it with Scrap&r to make it use a lot less EU. If constantly provided, it will take &6166,666 EU and 34 Scrap&r per mB.
ftbuniversity.matfab.desc3=A redstone signal will disable it.
ftbuniversity.matfab.desc4=Just a warning: &cthe Matter Fabricator's explosion radius is &l&nhuge&r&c if it gets too high of a voltage input&r. Do not let this happen.
ftbuniversity.matfab.desc5=The Matter Fabricator is &overy&r power-hungry, so its suggested to have a Nuclear Reactor running by this point.

ftbuniversity.ic2ev.title=Extreme Voltage
ftbuniversity.ic2ev.subtitle=Make HV Cables (yeah those)
ftbuniversity.ic2ev.desc1=&bHV Cables&r can transfer up to &6Extreme Voltage&r, carrying &61024 EU/t&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2ev.desc2=HV Cables have &64 tiers of insulation&r, protecting more from shocks.
ftbuniversity.ic2ev.task=HV Cables

ftbuniversity.eudetect.subtitle=制作一个 EU-Detector Cable
ftbuniversity.eudetect.desc=The &bEU-Detector Cable&r will emit a redstone signal while EU is passing through it.

ftbuniversity.eusplitter.title=Brexit Cable
ftbuniversity.eusplitter.subtitle=制作一个 EU-Splitter Cable
ftbuniversity.eusplitter.desc=The &bEU-Splitter Cable&r prevents EU from passing through it when given a redstone signal.

ftbuniversity.mfsu.title=Multi-Functional Storage Unit
ftbuniversity.mfsu.subtitle=制作一个 MFSU
ftbuniversity.mfsu.desc1=The &bMFSU&r can store up to &640,000,000 EU&r, and outputs at &6Extreme Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.mfsu.desc2=Oddly enough, the 6 Lapotron Crystals it's made with can each store 10,000,000 EU, so it really should store 60,000,000 EU. It doesn't, though.

ftbuniversity.hvtrans.title=HV↔EV
ftbuniversity.hvtrans.subtitle=制作一个(n) HV-Transformer
ftbuniversity.hvtrans.desc1=The &bHV-Transformer&r allows you to &6convert between High and Extreme Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.hvtrans.desc2=Transformers still haven't changed, you know what to do.

ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.title=Ctrl+C
ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.subtitle=制作一个 Scanner
ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.desc1=The &bScanner&r, using &6EV EU&r, will scan (some, not all) items you put into it, saving them to either the inserted &bCrystal Memory&r, or an adjacent &bPattern Storage&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.desc2=Scanning an item takes a &owhile&r, and uses &6850,000 EU&r total.
ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.desc3=When the item is done scanning, it will be destroyed and you will get the option to save the pattern.
ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.desc4=It will also display how much UU-Matter it needs (usually measured in micro-buckets (10µB=1mB).
ftbuniversity.ic2scanner.task=Storage

ftbuniversity.ic2replicator.title=Ctrl+V
ftbuniversity.ic2replicator.subtitle=制作一个 Replicator
ftbuniversity.ic2replicator.desc1=The &bReplicator&r, using &6EV EU&r, will take a pattern from an &6adjacent Pattern Storage&r and make its item, &6using UU-Matter&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2replicator.desc2=You can set it to &6craft one&r, &6craft infinitely&r, and also &6stop crafting&r.

ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.subtitle=制作一个 Terraformer
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc1=The &bTerraformer&r, using &6EV EU&r, will change the world around it based on the &bTFBP&r it has.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc2=A TFBP (Terraform Blueprint) does not change the biome or the weather, but makes changes on a block-by-block basis.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc3=• &6Chilling&r adds snow layers
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc4=• &6Cultivation&r turns Sand -> Dirt -> Grass Blocks, and plants plants.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc5=• &6Desertification&r turns Dirt -> Sand, destroys plants, and melts Snow and Ice.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc6=• &6Flatification&r breaks natural blocks above itself, and creates a layer of Dirt on its level.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc7=• &6Irrigation&r turns Sand -> Dirt -> Grass Blocks, spawns Water, forces plants to grow, etc.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.desc8=• &6Mushroom&r turns Dirt -> Mycelium and spawns mushrooms, as well as growing huge mushrooms.
ftbuniversity.ic2terraformer.task=Any TFBP

ftbuniversity.ic2iv.title=Insane Voltage
ftbuniversity.ic2iv.subtitle=Make Glass Fibre Cables
ftbuniversity.ic2iv.desc1=&bGlass Fibre Cables&r can transfer up to &6Insane Voltage&r, carrying &68192 EU/p&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2iv.desc2=They have the smallest EU loss of any Cable.
ftbuniversity.ic2iv.desc3=No machines use Insane Voltage, but remember it can transfer &nup to&r IV. The &6voltage is dependant only on the source&r, not the Cable.
ftbuniversity.ic2iv.desc4=Glass Fibre Cables will transfer every voltage as fast, since &6voltage is not current&r.

ftbuniversity.ivtrans.title=EV↔IV
ftbuniversity.ivtrans.subtitle=制作一个 EV-Transformer
ftbuniversity.ivtrans.desc1=The &bEV-Transformer&r allows you to &6convert between Extreme Voltage and Insane Voltage&r.
ftbuniversity.ivtrans.desc2=Pretty much nothing generates or uses Insane Voltage, so... there's not really a need for this.

ftbuniversity.econvert.title=Fine, You Can Have Yer Dang Converters
ftbuniversity.econvert.subtitle=Make Energy Converters
ftbuniversity.econvert.desc1=The mod &eEnergy Converters&r allows you to &6convert between FE and EU&r (remember, FE=RF).
ftbuniversity.econvert.desc2=However, as we want you to actually have to have to use EU generators, we're gating it all the way back here, at the end of IC2 progression. Sorry about that.
ftbuniversity.econvert.desc3=Place a &bConsumer&r of the type that you want to convert &nfrom&r, place a &bProducer&r of the type that you want to convert &ninto&r, then place an &bEnergy Bridge&r in-between, so it's touching both.
ftbuniversity.econvert.desc4=1 EU is equal to 4 RF.
ftbuniversity.econvert.task1=Consumers
ftbuniversity.econvert.task2=Producers

ftbuniversity.nanoarmor.title=NanoSuit
ftbuniversity.nanoarmor.subtitle=Make NanoSuit armor
ftbuniversity.nanoarmor.desc1=&bNanoSuit armor&r is powered by EU, and is &6roughly equivalent to Diamond armor&r.
ftbuniversity.nanoarmor.desc2=Each piece can &6hold up to 1,000,000 EU&r.

ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.title=QuantumSuit
ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.subtitle=Make QuantumSuit armor
ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.desc1=&bQuantumSuit armor&r is powered by EU, and is &6also equivalent to Diamond armor&r. However, each piece has some &6special feature&r.
ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.desc2=• The &bHelmet&r gives water breathing, automatically feeds you (Filled) Tin Cans, and cures Poison and Wither.
ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.desc3=• The &bBodyarmor&r works as a jetpack.
ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.desc4=• The &bLeggings&r increase your sprinting speed, even in water.
ftbuniversity.quantumsuit.desc5=• The &bBoots&r disable fall damage and increase your jump height when using the Boost Key (see controls, usually set to left control button).

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.title=Nuclear Energy, Industrial Style!
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.subtitle=Make radiation-proof armor
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.desc1=The &bNuclear Reactor&r is a fairly complex machine that can &6generate obscene amounts of EU&r using Uranium.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.desc2=When a Nuclear Reactor fails, it fails spectacularly. Meaning, it makes a &cmassive explosion&r and &cmakes the area radioactive&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.desc3=Two layers of &6Reinforced Stone&r (or &6Reinforced Glass&r) is enough to completely block the explosion, but still, be very careful.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.desc4=A Reactor generally fails due to overheating, so be careful with that.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear1.desc5=Firstly, 制作一个 set of &bradiation-proof armor&r. Without wearing this, holding Uranium in your inventory will irradiate you, dealing damage.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear2.title=Nuclear Fuel
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear2.subtitle=制作一个 Fuel Rod (Uranium)
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear2.desc=Nuclear Reactors are powered by &bFuel Rods&r, the most basic of which is simple &bUranium&b.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.title=Technically a Nuclear Reactor
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.subtitle=制作一个 Nuclear Reactor
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.desc1=A &bNuclear Reactor&r has 54 slots, though only 18 are available by default. The Reactor is only on when it is given a redstone signal.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.desc2=Each slot does not only hold items, but also &cheat&r. Heat is generated by fuels, and will spread to adjacent slots (or into the Reactor itself). If the Reactor gets too &chot&r, it will &cexplode&r, which is obviously bad.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.desc3=If you insert a &bFuel Rod (Uranium)&r, it will generate 5 EU/t and slowly heats up the Reactor at 4 hU per cycle. Over its entire life, it will generate 1,000,000 EU.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.desc4=&6Read &nevery&r&6 quest that depends on this one before doing anything more complex.&r

ftbuniversity.ic2rtg.title=Rumble Tumble Generator
ftbuniversity.ic2rtg.subtitle=制作一个 RTG-powered generator
ftbuniversity.ic2rtg.desc1=&bRTG&r is made out of Plutonium, which you can extract from Depleted Fuel Cells.
ftbuniversity.ic2rtg.desc2=When put into a &bRadioisotope Thermoelectric Generator&b, it will generate 1 EU/t forever. The amount doubles with each you put in, up to 32 EU/t from 6 RTG.
ftbuniversity.ic2rtg.desc3=The &bRadioisotope Heat Generator&r does the same, but instead of EU it generates up to 64 hU.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.title=Heat Dissipation
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.subtitle=Make heat dissipators
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.desc1=If the Nuclear Reactor is allowed to build up heat without being able to cool down, it will explode. These components can help prevent that.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.desc2=• The &bHeat Vent&r will &cdissipate 6 hU&r from itself every cycle. Place it next to a source of heat (Fuel Rods).
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.desc3=• The &bAdvanced Heat Vent&r is the same, but &6dissipates 12 hU&r instead.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.desc4=• The &bReactor Heat Vent&r &6moves 5 hU&r from the Reactor itself, then dissipates it.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.desc5=• The &bComponent Heat Vent&r dissipates &64 hU&r from each surrounding component.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.desc6=• The &bOverclocked Heat Vent&r &6moves 36 hU&r from the reactor to itself, then &6dissipates 20 hU&r from itself.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.1.task=Heat dissipators

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.title=Heat Movement
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.subtitle=Make Heat Exchangers
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.desc1=&bHeat Exchangers&r &6do not disssipate&r heat, instead they &6move heat around&r to allow more Vents access to it.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.desc2=• The basic &bHeat Exchanger&r will transfer &612 hU&r to/from each surrounding component, then transfer &64 hU&r to/fram the Reactor.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.desc3=• The &bAdvanced Heat Exchanger&r does the same, but at &624 hU&r and &68 hU&r instead.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.desc4=• The &bReactor Heat Exchanger&r transfers up to &672 hU&r with the Reactor, and none to components. It usually is at the same temperature as the Reactor. For these to cool down, they need a Component Heat Exchanger.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.desc5=• The &bComponent Heat Exchanger&r transfers up to &636 hU&r with adjacent components, and none with the Reactor.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.2.task=Heat Exchangers

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.3.title=Disposable Coolant
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.3.subtitle=Make Coolant/Condensators
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.3.desc1=&bCoolant&r and &bCondensators&r are single-use components that drain large amounts of heat, but are destroyed after.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.3.desc2=• The &b10k&r, &b30k&r, and &b60k Coolant Cells&r dissipate &610,000&r, &630,000&r, and &660,000 hU&r respectively.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.3.desc3=• The &bRSH-&r and &bLZH-Condensators&r dissipate &620,000&r and &6100,000 hU&r respectively.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.3.task=Coolant/Condensator

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.title=Efficiency
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.subtitle=Learn about fuel efficiency
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.desc1=&6Adjacent Fuel Rods work harder&r. Two adjacent Fuel Rods would make 4 times as much heat and energy.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.desc2=Fuel Rods emit "pulses" to adjacent slots. Fuel Rods that get a pulse get a boost. Since both Fuel Rods send and receive a pulse, both get the boost.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.desc3=Dual/Quad Fuel Rods send 2 and 4 pulses respectively.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.desc4=&bReflectors&r will reflect pulses, so you can have one Fuel Rod with 4 Reflectors, giving it an efficiency of 5.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.task1=Plural Fuel Rod
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.4.task2=Reflector

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.5.title=So Much Room For Activities
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.5.subtitle=Embiggen your Reactor
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.5.desc1=You can place a &bReactor Chamber&r on each face of the Nuclear Reactor to &6increase the amount of slots&r you can play with.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.5.desc2=Each Reactor Chamber adds another vertical slice of &66 slots&r. You can interact with Reactor Chambers as if you were using the Reactor block.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclearlink.title=This forum page has example reactor designs to copy
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclearlink.subtitle=It requires you download a program, but it's perfectly safe. Copy the Reactor Codes and then click "Paste Code" button in the Reactor Planner.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.6.title=The Candle That Burns Twice as Bright
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.6.subtitle=Make MOX Fuel
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.6.desc=&bMOX Fuel&r works &6twice as fast&r, and makes &6more energy the hotter it is&r (up to 5 times normal at 99.9%% heat).
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear3.6.task=MOX Fuel

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.title=Fluid Reactors
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.subtitle=制作一个 Fluid Reactor
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.desc1=A normal Nuclear Reactor directly generates EU. A &bFluid Reactor&r instead prioritizes generating heat, which spins turbines, &6creating vastly more EU&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.desc2=To build a Fluid Reactor, 制作一个 5x5x5 cube out of &bReactor Pressure Vessels&r, with a 3x3x3 space within housing a Reactor full with Chambers.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.desc3=You can &6replace any Reactor Pressure Vessel&r with the following:
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.desc4=• The &bReactor Access Hatch&r allows you to &6open the GUI&r, as well as allowing &6automatic item transfer&r through itself.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.desc5=• The &bReactor Redstone Port&r will &6turn on/off the Reactor&r based on if it has a &6redstone signal&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear4.desc6=• The &bReactor Fluid Port&r allows the &6insertion of Coolant&r and &6extraction of Hot Coolant&r via pipes.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear5.title=You're Hot, Then You're Cold
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear5.subtitle=Convert Coolant to Hot Coolant
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear5.desc1=Generating and dissipating heat is the goal of Fluid Reactors.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear5.desc2=When heat is dissipated, &bCoolant&r will be converted into &bHot Coolant&r. That means you can't just make the Reactor hot, you have to use Vents to cool it down too.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear5.desc3=You can manually insert Coolant and extract Hot Coolant in fluid-containing-items, or automatically do it via
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear5.desc4=Ideally, your Fluid Reactor would be producing enough Hot Coolant to &6run several&r Liquid Heat Exchangers (and thus, every step after) &6at once&r.

ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear6.subtitle=制作一个 Liquid Heat Exchanger
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear6.desc1=The &bLiquid Heat Exchanger&r converts Hot Coolant to Coolant, &6generating and pushing heat out the orange face&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear6.desc2=It has room for up to 10 &bHeat Conductors&r; you need 2 for it to work at all.
ftbuniversity.ic2nuclear6.desc3=Hot Coolant is only cooled down if it has something to push heat into.

ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.subtitle=制作一个 Steam Boiler
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc1=The &bSteam Boiler&r uses heat to &6convert 1mB of Water to 100mB of Steam&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc2=You cannot manually insert Water, you have to use pipes.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc3=You can control the flow of Water, to limit how much Steam is produced.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc4=You can also control the pressure, measured in &6bars&r. At &6221+ bars, Superheated Steam&r is produced instead.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc5=If the temperature passes 500C, &cit will explode&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc6=If it fills up with Steam and doesn't have it extracted, it will release it, damaging nearby entities.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc7=The &6calcification&r of the Steam Boiler will increase as Water is boiled. At 100%%, it will stop working, and will have to be broken and replaced.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc8=To prevent calcification, use &6Distilled Water&r instead (which can be a produced in a future step).
ftbuniversity.ic2steamboiler.desc9=For the optimal setup, set it to &6convert 1mB/t&r at &6221 Bar&r, creating Superheated Steam.

ftbuniversity.ic2steamturbine.subtitle=制作一个 Steam Turbine and a Steam Turbine
ftbuniversity.ic2steamturbine.desc1=The &bSteam Turbine&r, when a &bSteam Turbine&r is placed in it (that won't get confusing, nope), will &6convert Steam into Kinetic Energy&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamturbine.desc2=When this happens, it generates something as a byproduct. &6Steam produces Distilled Water, and Superheated Steam produces Steam.&r
ftbuniversity.ic2steamturbine.desc3=That means, using the optimal setup, you can &6put two Steam Turbines on top of each other&r, the first converting Superheated Steam to Steam, the second converting Steam to Distilled Water.
ftbuniversity.ic2steamturbine.desc4=If you've been doing it right, everything should be making awful steam explosion noises and particles. &6See the quest above for how to fix that.&r

ftbuniversity.ic2condenser.subtitle=制作一个 Condenser
ftbuniversity.ic2condenser.desc1=The &bCondenser&r converts Steam into Distilled Water.
ftbuniversity.ic2condenser.desc2=It is &6extremely essential when using Steam Turbines&r, as otherwise it will create constant explosions, which is awful and annoying &oand took me 4 freaking hours to figure out &lwhy argh&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2condenser.desc3=You can insert Heat Vents to speed it up, and only then does it need EU.

ftbuniversity.ic2kineticgen.subtitle=制作一个 Kinetic Generator
ftbuniversity.ic2kineticgen.desc1=The &bKinetic Generator&r converts kinetic energy into EU.
ftbuniversity.ic2kineticgen.desc2=Kinetic energy works a lot like heat: it has no pipes and connections must be directly touching.
ftbuniversity.ic2kineticgen.desc3=You can use a Wrench (New) to manually rotate kU generators and users to face each other.

ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.title=Let's Smoke This Beer!
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.subtitle=Set up a brewery
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.desc1=Alcohol, as everyone knows, gives you magical potion effects.
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.desc2=To begin, place a &bScaffold&r and use an &bEmpty Booze Barrel&r on it.
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.desc3=The type of beer depends on what you put in next. There are three things that matter: the Solids:Water ratio, the Hops:Wheat ratio, and the time allowed to ferment.
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.desc4=Honestly, the best way to figure this out would be to look it up. There's a lot of spreadsheets for getting the optimal alcohol, but that can't exactly be put into a quest.
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.desc5=When you're done fermenting (minimum half an hour, maximum 24 hours), use a &bTreetap&r on the Booze Barrel, then use a &bStone Mug&r on it to take some out.
ftbuniversity.ic2brew1.task=Brewable items

###Immersive Engineering
ftbuniversity.iechap.title=Immersive Engineering

ftbuniversity.engineersmanual.title=RTFM
ftbuniversity.engineersmanual.subtitle=Get the Engineer's Manual
ftbuniversity.engineersmanual.desc=The &bEngineer's Manual&r is generally the best place for information on Immersive Engineering.

ftbuniversity.iepipe.title=Pipe Dream
ftbuniversity.iepipe.subtitle=Make Fluid Pipe
ftbuniversity.iepipe.desc1=&bFluid Pipes&r are used to transfer fluids.
ftbuniversity.iepipe.desc2=They do not pull on their own; &6fluids must be pushed into them&r.
ftbuniversity.iepipe.desc3=You can use the &6Engineer's Hammer&r to disable connections. Using &6Scaffolding&r on a Pipe will cover it.

ftbuniversity.iepump.subtitle=制作一个 Fluid Pump
ftbuniversity.iepump.desc1=The &bFluid Pump&r has two uses: &6collecting in-world fluids&r, and &6quickly extracting from tanks&r.
ftbuniversity.iepump.desc2=To pump in-world fluids, place the Fluid Pump &6directly above the fluid&r, provide it &6RF&r from the top, and give it a &6redstone signal&r. You will need to use an &6Engineer's Hammer&r to set which side to output the pumped fluid.
ftbuniversity.iepump.desc3=To extract from tanks, place the Fluid Pump &6directly adjacent to the tank&r, with the side touching it &6set to input&r. When given a &6redstone signal&r, it will pull fluids out of that tank and &6push it out of any output sides&r. This &6does not require RF&r.

ftbuniversity.ieconveyor.subtitle=Make some Conveyor Belts
ftbuniversity.ieconveyor.desc1=&bConveyor Belts&r will &6move entities&r in the direction they are pointed. This is pretty good for early-game automation, and they just frankly look great.
ftbuniversity.ieconveyor.desc2=Click it with an Engineer's Hammer to turn it, and &6sneak click&r to set if it's at an incline.
ftbuniversity.ieconveyor.desc3=If a Conveyor Belt is pointed at an inventory, it will automatically deposit items into it.
ftbuniversity.ieconveyor.desc4=Conveyor Belts can be dyed by right-clicking, and a redstone signal will disable them.

ftbuniversity.ieotherbelts.title=Belts for Fancy-Pants
ftbuniversity.ieotherbelts.subtitle=Make the other Conveyor Belts
ftbuniversity.ieotherbelts.desc1=&bVertical Conveyor Belts&r will &6move items up&r, and then onto the block the top one is placed on.
ftbuniversity.ieotherbelts.desc2=&bDropping Conveyor Belts&r will &6drop items&r, either into the world or into the inventory directly below.
ftbuniversity.ieotherbelts.desc3=&bSplitting Conveyor Belts&r will &6alternate between sending things left or right&r.
ftbuniversity.ieotherbelts.desc4=&bExtractor Conveyor Belts&r will &6pull items out of the inventory it is facing&r and put them on the Conveyor Belt. Sneak click with an Engineer's Hammer to set which side to pull from, and click with Wire Cutters to choose how often it pulls.

ftbuniversity.iecoveredbelt.title=Tucked In
ftbuniversity.iecoveredbelt.subtitle=制作一个 Covered Conveyor Belt
ftbuniversity.iecoveredbelt.desc1=One of the biggest problems with Conveyor Belts is that, if you get too close, you'll pick up the items they are carrying.
ftbuniversity.iecoveredbelt.desc2=&bCovered Conveyor Belts'&r items cannot be picked up, which solves that problem.
ftbuniversity.iecoveredbelt.desc3=&6Almost every Belt type has a Covered version.&r
ftbuniversity.iecoveredbelt.task=Any Covered Belt

ftbuniversity.ierouter.subtitle=制作一个 Item Router
ftbuniversity.ierouter.desc1=The &bItem Router&r will send items input into the direction that you set.
ftbuniversity.ierouter.desc2=Each side has a color. In the GUI, you can set a whitelist of 8 items per color-coded side, and those items will be output through that side.
ftbuniversity.ierouter.desc3=You can also toggle &6OreDictionary&r, &6NBT&r, and &6Fuzzy Filters&r per side.

ftbuniversity.engineershammer.title=Percussive Maintenance
ftbuniversity.engineershammer.subtitle=制作一个 Engineer's Hammer
ftbuniversity.engineershammer.desc=The &bEngineer's Hammer&r is arguably the most important tool in Immersive Engineering. It is required to form multiblocks and configure some other specific machines.

ftbuniversity.iecokeoven.title=Time to Cook
ftbuniversity.iecokeoven.subtitle=Construct a Coke Oven
ftbuniversity.iecokeoven.desc1=The &bCoke Oven&r is the only way to get &6Coal Coke&r and &6Creosote Oil&r.
ftbuniversity.iecokeoven.desc2=制作一个 &63x3x3 cube of Coke Bricks&r, then &6right-click the center of any face with an Engineer's Hammer&r to form it.

ftbuniversity.ieblastfurnace.title=Blasting Off
ftbuniversity.ieblastfurnace.subtitle=Construct a Crude Blast Furnace
ftbuniversity.ieblastfurnace.desc1=The &bCrude Blast Furnace&r allows you to &6burn Iron with Coal Coke to get Steel&r.
ftbuniversity.ieblastfurnace.desc2=Like the Coke Oven, 制作一个 &63x3x3 cube of Blast Bricks then click with an Engineer's Hammer&r to form it.
ftbuniversity.ieblastfurnace.desc3=The Crude Blast Furnace &ccannot be automated&r.

ftbuniversity.improvedblastfurnace.title=Blasting Off Again!
ftbuniversity.improvedblastfurnace.subtitle=Construct the Improved Blast Furnace
ftbuniversity.improvedblastfurnace.desc1=The &bImproved Blast Furnace&r works the same as a Crude Blast Furnace, except &6it can be automated&r. Inputs must be entered through the top, Steel is output through the front, and Slag is output through the back.
ftbuniversity.improvedblastfurnace.desc2=Again, &6click an Engineer's Hammer on the center of any face&r to form it.

ftbuniversity.blastfurnacepreheaters.title=Bigger, Better, Faster, Stronger
ftbuniversity.blastfurnacepreheaters.subtitle=制作一个 pair of Blast Furnace Preheaters
ftbuniversity.blastfurnacepreheaters.desc=&bBlast Furnace Preheaters&r can be placed on either side of the Improved Blast Furnace to speed them up, when provided RF through their tops.

ftbuniversity.iewindmill.title=Set and Forget
ftbuniversity.iewindmill.subtitle=Set up a Wind Mill
ftbuniversity.iewindmill.desc1=The &bWind Mill&r, when placed on a &bKinetic Dynamo&r, will generate RF based on the current wind speed (which itself is based on weather, elevation, and certain other factors).
ftbuniversity.iewindmill.desc2=You can install up to 8 &bWindmill Sails&r to increase this amount.
ftbuniversity.iewindmill.desc3=When placed above y=200, in a thunder storm, with 8 Windmill Sails, the Wind Mill will generate &6100 RF/t maximum&r.

ftbuniversity.waterwheel.title=Every Expert Pack's Early Generator
ftbuniversity.waterwheel.subtitle=Set up a Water Wheel
ftbuniversity.waterwheel.desc1=The &bWater Wheel&r, when placed on a &bKinetic Dynamo&r, will generate RF when the edges are pushed by flowing Water.
ftbuniversity.waterwheel.desc2=&6The more flowing water it is touching, the more RF/t it makes (at a maximum of 30RF/t).&r It generates at that speed infinitely, unless the water is removed or changed.
ftbuniversity.waterwheel.desc3=You can have &6up to three Water Wheels per Kinetic Dynamo&r, simply by placing them on the same axis.

ftbuniversity.iecables.title=Danger Danger! High Voltage!
ftbuniversity.iecables.subtitle=Set up some Wires
ftbuniversity.iecables.desc1=Immersive Engineering's Wires are unique. Instead of placing down a block for every part of the path, you only place connections.
ftbuniversity.iecables.desc2=&bWire Connectors&r are placed on machines where you want to &6input or extract RF&r from. You can only connect a Wire Connector to &6one destination&r.
ftbuniversity.iecables.desc3=&bWire Relays&r are used to &6connect Wire Connectors&r. If you have a room full of machines, they'd all have a Wire Connector on them, all of them would connect to the same Wire Relay, and then the Wire Relay would connect to a source of energy somewhere else.
ftbuniversity.iecables.desc4=&bWire Coils&r are clicked on two parts (Connectors/Relays) to connect them. They have a maximum range and cannot go through blocks.
ftbuniversity.iecables.desc5=Wires, Connectors, and Relays come in three tiers, &6LV&r, &6MV&r, and &6HV&r. Higher tiers can move more RF/t (&62,048&r, &68,192&r, and &632,768&r respectively). If more RF than it can handle tries to flow through, that wire will burn up.
ftbuniversity.iecables.desc6=Connectors and Relays &6only work with Wires of the same voltage&r. &cUninsulated Wires will damage anything that touches them.&r Note that there are no Insulated HV Wire Coils.
ftbuniversity.iecables.task1=Any Wire Connector
ftbuniversity.iecables.task2=Any Wire Relay
ftbuniversity.iecables.task3=Any Wire Coil
ftbuniversity.iecables.rewards=Wire Coils

ftbuniversity.iewirecutters.title=Snip Snap Snip Snap Snip Snap
ftbuniversity.iewirecutters.subtitle=Make Engineer's Wire Cutters
ftbuniversity.iewirecutters.desc=&bEngineer's Wire Cutters&r will remove all Wire Coils from a Connector/Relay when used on it.

ftbuniversity.ietransformers.title=Robots In Disguise
ftbuniversity.ietransformers.subtitle=制作一个 Transformer
ftbuniversity.ietransformers.desc1=&bTransformers&r allow you to &6convert between two voltages&r. This allows you to, for instance, use LV Wires for each generator, then group them all together into a single MV Wire that can carry their combined RF/t.
ftbuniversity.ietransformers.desc2=The regular Transformer converts between LV and MV. The &bHV Transformer&r converts between MV and HV.
ftbuniversity.ietransformers.task=Either Transformer

ftbuniversity.breakerswitch.title=ᴹᴱᴱᴾ
ftbuniversity.breakerswitch.subtitle=制作一个 Breaker Switch
ftbuniversity.breakerswitch.desc=A &bBreaker Switch&r can have wires connected to either side, and &6will only allow power through them when it is activated&r.

ftbuniversity.iecapacitors.title=Power Bank
ftbuniversity.iecapacitors.subtitle=制作一个 Capacitor
ftbuniversity.iecapacitors.desc1=&bCapacitors&r &6store RF&r, and have multiple tiers. In order, they store &6100,000RF&r, &61,000,000RF&r, and &64,000,000RF&r.
ftbuniversity.iecapacitors.desc2=Capacitors have &6no GUI&r. To set which sides are input or output, &6use an Engineer's Hammer on them&r. Blue=in, orange=out.
ftbuniversity.iecapacitors.task=Any Capacitor

ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.subtitle=制作一个 Engineer's Workbench
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.desc1=The &bEngineer's Workbenches&r offer exclusive crafting recipes, set by the &bEngineer's Blueprint&r inserted into them.
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.desc2=Insert the Blueprint, then hover over one of the items on the right and it will say which items and their amounts that you need. Once those requirements are met, you can pull the item out of the right slots.
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.desc3=The Blueprints specified in this quest &6can be crafted&r, however there are two others that you can only get by &6trading with a Villager&r.
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.desc4=Certain items, like the &6Revolver&r and the &6Mining Drill&r can be upgraded in the Workbench.
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.task=Any craftable Blueprint
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.rewards=Villager Blueprints
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.reward1=Specialized Projectiles
ftbuniversity.engineersworkbench.reward2=Arc Furnace Electrodes
ftbuniversity.grabbags.rewards=Random Shader Grabbag

ftbuniversity.ieminingdrill.drill=Pierce the Heavens!
ftbuniversity.ieminingdrill.subtitle=制作一个 Mining Drill
ftbuniversity.ieminingdrill.desc1=The &bMining Drill&r is a modular tool that can &6dig through all Dirt and Stone type blocks&r, with the mining level based on the &6Drill Head&r.
ftbuniversity.ieminingdrill.desc2=To install a Drill Head, put the Drill in the left slot of an Engineer's Workbench, and then put the Head in the top center slot.
ftbuniversity.ieminingdrill.desc3=The Mining Drill is &6powered by Biodiesel&r, not RF.
ftbuniversity.ieminingdrill.desc4=The mining area is set by the Drill Head you use. Sneaking will make you mine a single block at a time.

ftbuniversity.miningdrillupgrades.title=Drill Upgrades
ftbuniversity.miningdrillupgrades.subtitle=制作一个y Mining Drill Upgrade
ftbuniversity.miningdrillupgrades.desc1=Up to 3 &bMining Drill upgrades&r can be installed on a Mining Drill by putting it in the left slot of an Engineer's Workbench and upgrades in the center slots.
ftbuniversity.miningdrillupgrades.desc2=The upgrade's &6tooltip explains when it does&r.
ftbuniversity.miningdrillupgrades.task=Any Mining Drill Upgrade

ftbuniversity.ierevolver.title=The Real Treasure Was the Guns We Made Along the Way
ftbuniversity.ierevolver.subtitle=制作一个 Revolver
ftbuniversity.ierevolver.desc1=The &bRevolver&r is a ranged weapon that can accept several types of ammo. To insert the ammo, sneak right-click it and manually &6insert up to 8 Cartridges&r. Right-click to fire the top Cartridge, and it will rotate all slots counterclockwise.
ftbuniversity.ierevolver.desc2=A &6Speedloader&r can also be filled with Cartridges, and it will automatically reload the Revolver if fired while empty.
ftbuniversity.ierevolver.desc3=There are &611 types of Cartridge&r, each having something unique about it. &6Read the Engineer's Manual&r page for them for an explanation for each.
ftbuniversity.ierevolver.desc4=For reference, &6a Casull Cartridge deals 7.5 hearts of damage&r.
ftbuniversity.ierevolver.task=Any Cartridge

ftbuniversity.ierevolverupgrades.title=The Power of GUN
ftbuniversity.ierevolverupgrades.subtitle=制作一个 Revolver upgrade
ftbuniversity.ierevolverupgrades.desc1=Up to 2 &bRevolver upgrades&r can be installed on a Revolver by putting the Revolver in the left slot of an Engineer's Workbench and upgrades in the center slots.
ftbuniversity.ierevolverupgrades.desc2=The upgrade's &6tooltip explains what it does&r.
ftbuniversity.ierevolverupgrades.task=Any Revolver Upgrade

ftbuniversity.iechemthrower.title=Squirt Gun
ftbuniversity.iechemthrower.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Thrower
ftbuniversity.iechemthrower.desc1=The &bChemical Thrower&r will &6shoot whatever fluid/gas it has&r in its internal tank. If that fluid is flammable, you can sneak right-click to toggle lighting it on fire.
ftbuniversity.iechemthrower.desc2=There's no in-game list of what each fluid does, but it's pretty self-evident. Lava makes fires, Water puts out fires, Oils/Diesels can be lit on fire, etc.

ftbuniversity.chemthrowerupgrades.title=Chemical Thrower Upgrades
ftbuniversity.chemthrowerupgrades.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Thrower upgrade
ftbuniversity.chemthrowerupgrades.desc1=Up to 2 &bChemical Thrower upgrades&r can be installed on a Chemical Thrower by putting the Thrower in the left slot of an Engineer's Workbench and upgrades in the center slots.
ftbuniversity.chemthrowerupgrades.desc2=The upgrade's &6tooltip explains what it does&r.
ftbuniversity.chemthrowerupgrades.task=Any Chemical Thrower Upgrade

ftbuniversity.ierailgun.title=A Certain Scientific One, At That
ftbuniversity.ierailgun.subtitle=制作一个 Railgun
ftbuniversity.ierailgun.desc1=The &bRailgun&r uses a large amount of RF to &6shoot Aluminum/Iron/Steel Rods&r, or &6Graphite Electrodes&r. To shoot, hold right-click and then release when the charger reaches 99.
ftbuniversity.ierailgun.desc2=The higher tiers of ammo deal more damage (&6in same order as above: 13, 15, 18, and 24 points&r).
ftbuniversity.ierailgun.desc3=The Railgun uses a &olot&r of RF, so &6it's suggested that you have a way to charge it on the go&r.

ftbuniversity.railgunups.title=Railgun Upgrades
ftbuniversity.railgunups.subtitle=制作一个 Railgun upgrade
ftbuniversity.railgunups.desc1=Up to 2 &bRailgun upgrades&r can be installed on a Railgun by putting it in the left slot of an Engineer's Workbench and upgrades in the center slots.
ftbuniversity.railgunups.desc2=The upgrade's &6tooltip explains what it does&r.
ftbuniversity.railgunups.task=Any Railgun Upgrade

ftbuniversity.iechargingstation.subtitle=制作一个 Charging Station
ftbuniversity.iechargingstation.desc1=The &bCharging Station&r will &6charge any item&r you insert into it with RF. It has &6no GUI&r, so just click it to insert or remove an item.
ftbuniversity.iechargingstation.desc2=&6RF can only be inserted via the bottom or the back sides.&r

ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.title=Arguably OP Farm
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.subtitle=制作一个 Garden Cloche
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.desc1=The &bGarden Cloche&r will &6grow and harvest crops&r within itself. It's very fast and honestly weirdly cheap, for how good it is.
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.desc2=It requires a &6steady supply of Water and RF&r. You can also give it fertilizer in the bottom left slot.
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.desc3=Insert a seed into the top center slot, and its required soil underneath. &6Pretty nuch every crop is compatible&r, even mushrooms, Ender Lilys, and Red Orchids!
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.desc4=The harvested crop will be pushed out of the &6front-center&r.
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.desc5=Water and fertilizer can be input through the &6bottom&r, &6bottom-front&r, or &6bottom-back&r.
ftbuniversity.iegardencloche.desc6=RF can be input through the &6top&r, &6bottom-left&r, or &6bottom-right&r.

ftbuniversity.iereadthefrickenbook.desc=&6See the Engineer's Manual&r for construction instructions.

ftbuniversity.iemetalpress.title=Plates and Gears and Rods, Oh My!
ftbuniversity.iemetalpress.subtitle=Construct a Metal Press
ftbuniversity.iemetalpress.desc1=The &bMetal Press&r is likely to be one of the first machines you make. It gives &6cheaper recipes for Plates, Gears, Rods, etc&r, using &6Metal Press Molds&r (which can only be made in the Engineer's Workbench).
ftbuniversity.iemetalpress.desc2=Insert items, give it the correct Mold, and then it will use RF (which is entered from the top) to press the item according to the Mold. Items will be output at the end, into an inventory or Conveyor Belt.
ftbuniversity.iemetalpress.task=Look at a completed Metal Press

ftbuniversity.ieassembler.title=Autocrafting
ftbuniversity.ieassembler.subtitle=Construct an Assembler
ftbuniversity.ieassembler.desc1=The &bAssembler&r can &6automatically craft&r up to three recipes using items and fluids inserted into it.
ftbuniversity.ieassembler.desc2=The result of the first recipe can be used as an ingredient in the second recipe, and so on. The final non-empty recipe result will be output from the back.
ftbuniversity.ieassembler.desc3=If a recipe would use fluids (say, Treated Wood), it can use the contents of the tanks instead of a bucket item.
ftbuniversity.ieassembler.desc4=Power can enter the top; items, the front center; fluids, the front bottom.
ftbuniversity.ieassembler.task=Look at a completed Assembler

ftbuniversity.ieindussqueeze.title=Industrial Squeezer
ftbuniversity.ieindussqueeze.subtitle=Construct an Industrial Squeezer
ftbuniversity.ieindussqueeze.desc=The &bIndustrial Squeezer&r presses the juices out of organic material, like seeds.
ftbuniversity.ieindussqueeze.task=Look at a completed Squeezer

ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.title=Arc Furnace
ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.subtitle=Construct an Arc Furnace
ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.desc1=The &bArc Furnace&r &6doubles ores and smelts alloys&r, producing Slag as a byproduct.
ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.desc2=To function, the Arc Furnace &6requires 3 Graphite Electrodes&r in the top slots. These will wear down as the Arc Furnace runs, and must be replaced when broken.
ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.desc3=The item to be worked goes in the left; the Arc Furnace will &6smelt all slots at the same time&r. In the case of alloying, the main part goes in the left and the secondary ingredients go on the right.
ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.desc4=Items are inserted in the top and pulled out of the Cauldron; Power is inserted in the three slots in the back; Slag is pulled out of the face under the power slots.
ftbuniversity.iearcfurnace.task=Look at a completed Arc Furnace

ftbuniversity.iesilo.title=Items, Not Missiles
ftbuniversity.iesilo.subtitle=Construct a Silo
ftbuniversity.iesilo.desc1=A &bSilo&r can &6hold 41,472 of a single item&r (which is 648 stacks, or 24 chests' worth).
ftbuniversity.iesilo.desc2=Items must be input through the top, and extracted from the bottom. Giving the bottom block a redstone signal will make it auto-output.
ftbuniversity.iesilo.task=Look at a completed Silo

ftbuniversity.iecrusher.title=Crushinator
ftbuniversity.iecrusher.subtitle=Construct a Crusher
ftbuniversity.iecrusher.desc=The &bCrusher&r will &6double ores, grind blocks, and kill mobs&r.
ftbuniversity.iecrusher.task=Look at a completed Crusher

ftbuniversity.ieindusferment.title=Industrial Fermenter
ftbuniversity.ieindusferment.subtitle=Construct an Industrial Fermenter
ftbuniversity.ieindusferment.desc=The &bFermenter&r is used to convert certain items into &6Ethanol&r.
ftbuniversity.ieindusferment.task=Look at a completed Industrial Fermenter

ftbuniversity.iemixer.title=Twitchn't
ftbuniversity.iemixer.subtitle=Construct a Mixer
ftbuniversity.iemixer.desc=The &bMixer&r combines items and fluids to &6create new fluids&r.
ftbuniversity.iemixer.task=Look at a completed Mixer

ftbuniversity.iecoresample.title=To the Core
ftbuniversity.iecoresample.subtitle=制作一个 Core Sample Drill
ftbuniversity.iecoresample.desc1=The &bCore Sample Drill&r, once placed and powered, can be right-clicked to get a &6Core Sample&r.
ftbuniversity.iecoresample.desc2=Core Samples will say what mineral/fluid deposit is in that chunk, which is important information for the Excavator and Pumpjack.

ftbuniversity.ieexcavator.title=Excavator
ftbuniversity.ieexcavator.subtitle=Construct an Excavator
ftbuniversity.ieexcavator.desc1=The &bExcavator&r uses a large amount of RF/t to &6pull ores from its chunk's mineral deposit&r.
ftbuniversity.ieexcavator.desc2=This allows you to get a rather large amount of ores, if the chunk has a mineral deposit.

ftbuniversity.ippumpjack.title=Pumpjack
ftbuniversity.ippumpjack.subtitle=Construct a Pumpjack
ftbuniversity.ippumpjack.desc1=&eImmersive Petroleum&r is an addon for Immersive Engineering that adds oil.
ftbuniversity.ippumpjack.desc2=The &bPumpjack&r uses RF to &6pull fluids from its chunk's fluid deposit&r, and will deposit it out the sides.
ftbuniversity.ippumpjack.task=Look at a completed Pumpjack

ftbuniversity.ipdisttower.title=Distillation Tower
ftbuniversity.ipdisttower.subtitle=Construct a Distillation Tower
ftbuniversity.ipdisttower.desc1=The &bDistillation Tower&r will use RF to &6convert Oil into Gasoline, Diesel, and Lubricant&r. It also produces &6Bitumen&r, which is automatically ejected out the back.
ftbuniversity.ipdisttower.desc2=The Distillation Tower is the largest multiblock, so you should probably &6use the Projector&r.
ftbuniversity.ipdisttower.desc3=Diesel can power the Diesel Generator; Gasoline can power the Motorboat and Portable Generator.
ftbuniversity.ipdisttower.task=Look at a completed Distillation Tower

ftbuniversity.iplubecan.subtitle=制作一个 Lubricant Can
ftbuniversity.iplubecan.desc=A full &bLubricant Can&r can be &6clicked on a Pumpjack, Excavator, or Crusher to speed them up&r.

ftbuniversity.ipautolube.subtitle=制作一个 Automated Lubricator
ftbuniversity.ipautolube.desc1=An &bAutomatic Lubricator&r can be &6placed adjacent to a Pumpjack, Excavator, or Crusher to speed them up&r while it has a supply of Lubricant.
ftbuniversity.ipautolube.desc2=Hold the Automatic Lubricator to see where exactly you need to place it for it to work.

ftbuniversity.iebottlingmachine.title=From the Tap
ftbuniversity.iebottlingmachine.subtitle=Construct a Bottling Machine
ftbuniversity.iebottlingmachine.desc=The &bBottling Machine&r will &bfill a fluid container with a fluid&r.
ftbuniversity.iebottlingmachine.task=Look at a completed Bottling Machine

ftbuniversity.ietank.title=Not-Quite-Portable Tank
ftbuniversity.ietank.subtitle=Construct a Fluid Tank
ftbuniversity.ietank.desc1=The &bFluid Tank&r can &6store 512 buckets&r of a single fluid. You can right-click a Bucket on it to insert or extract fluid.
ftbuniversity.ietank.desc2=Fluids can be input through the top, and extracted from the bottom. Giving the bottom block a redstone signal will make it auto-output.
ftbuniversity.ietank.task=Look at a completed Fluid Tank

ftbuniversity.ieautoworkbench.title=Automated Engineer's Workbench
ftbuniversity.ieautoworkbench.subtitle=Construct an Automated Engineer's Workbench
ftbuniversity.ieautoworkbench.desc1=The &bAutomated Engineer's Workbench&r will &6automatically craft a single Engineer's Blueprint recipe&r.
ftbuniversity.ieautoworkbench.desc2=Insert an Engineer's Blueprint, and choose which item you want to autocraft. When it has the items required (and power, obviously), it will craft and output that item.
ftbuniversity.ieautoworkbench.task=Look at a completed Automated Engineer's Workbench

ftbuniversity.ierefinery.title=I Feel Fine
ftbuniversity.ierefinery.subtitle=制作一个 Refinery
ftbuniversity.ierefinery.desc=The &bRefinery&r is used to &6combine Plant Oil and Ethanol to make Biodiesel&r, which can be used for the Diesel Generator or the Mining Drill.
ftbuniversity.ierefinery.task=Look at a completed Refinery

ftbuniversity.ielightningrod.title=Thunder, Feel the Thunder
ftbuniversity.ielightningrod.subtitle=Construct a Lightning Rod
ftbuniversity.ielightningrod.desc1=The &bLightning Rod&r generates a &6massive amount of RF when it gets hit by lightning&r.
ftbuniversity.ielightningrod.desc2=&6Stack Steel Fences&r in a pole centered on the Lightning Rod to increase the chances of getting struck (though it still only works during storms).
ftbuniversity.ielightningrod.desc3=You can also 制作一个 plane of Steel Fences connected to the topmost Fence to increase the chances further.
ftbuniversity.ielightningrod.task=Look at a completed Lightning Rod

ftbuniversity.iedieselgen.title=Eco-Friendly™
ftbuniversity.iedieselgen.subtitle=Construct a Diesel Generator
ftbuniversity.iedieselgen.desc1=The &bDiesel Generator&r &6generates RF from Biodiesel or Diesel&r.
ftbuniversity.iedieselgen.desc2=A bucket of &6Biodiesel generates 512,000RF&r, and a bucket of &6Disel generates 819,200RF&r.
ftbuniversity.iedieselgen.task=Look at a completed Diesel Generator

ftbuniversity.ipportagen.subtitle=制作一个 Portable Generator
ftbuniversity.ipportagen.desc1=The &bPortable Generator&r generates &651,200RF per bucket of Gasoline&r.
ftbuniversity.ipportagen.desc2=Power can only be output through Wires connected directly to the Generator.

###PneumaticCraft: Repressurized
ftbuniversity.pneuchap.title=PneumaticCraft: Repressurized

ftbuniversity.pneubook.title=New Matics
ftbuniversity.pneubook.subtitle=Get the PCN:R Manual
ftbuniversity.pneubook.desc1=&ePneumaticCraft: Repressurized&r is a very unique mod, in that it doesn't use RF at all and instead uses &6air pressure&r.
ftbuniversity.pneubook.desc2=The &bPCN:R Manual&r has information on pretty much everything the mod adds. Unlock pages by completing advancements.
ftbuniversity.pneubook.desc3=&cNot everything in PneumaticCraft will have a quest&r; be sure to poke around the Manual to see what else is available.

ftbuniversity.whatispressure.title=What Is Pressure?
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.subtitle=Learn about air pressure
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.desc1=&bAir pressure&r is what powers most PneumaticCraft machines, and is &6measured in &nbars&r. The more bars, the higher the pressure.
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.desc2=Air moves from high-pressure areas to low-pressure areas, and will try to equalize throughout the system.
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.desc3=If the air pressure in a machine is too high, the machine will explode.
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.desc4=PneumaticCraft machines and tools all have a specific volume (measured in mL) that represents how much air they hold at 0 bar. This can be &6increased with Volume Upgrades&r.
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.desc5=Machines use compressed air to operate, which consequently lowers the air pressure.
ftbuniversity.whatispressure.desc6=&6Read the PCN:R Manual&r for a more thorough explanation.

ftbuniversity.whatisheat.title=What is Heat?
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.subtitle=Learn about heat
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.desc1=&bHeat&r is another mechanic unique to PneumaticCraft.
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.desc2=&6Heat disperses&r to adjacent blocks, including air.
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.desc3=If certain heat sources have their heat dispersed entirely, &6it can convert to a different block&r entirely (Lava to Obsidian, etc).
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.desc4=You can prevent heat from radiating into the air by &6covering the block&r in anything that isn't air.
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.desc5=Some blocks require an external source of heat, and some generate heat that has to be removed.
ftbuniversity.whatisheat.desc6=&6Touching extreme hot or cold will damage you.&r

ftbuniversity.compressediron.title=Untuple Compressed Iron Ingot
ftbuniversity.compressediron.subtitle=Get a Compressed Iron Ingot
ftbuniversity.compressediron.desc1=&bCompressed Iron&r is a new material added by PneumaticCraft, and is used by pretty much everything in the mod.
ftbuniversity.compressediron.desc2=Get it by &6throwing down some Iron Ingots/Blocks, then creating an explosion nearby&r.

ftbuniversity.pressuretube.title=Pressure Pushing Down On Me
ftbuniversity.pressuretube.subtitle=Make some Pressure Tubes
ftbuniversity.pressuretube.desc1=&bPressure Tubes&r &6carry compressed air&r. If the pressure inside it reaches 5.0 bar, it will burst.
ftbuniversity.pressuretube.desc2=&6Air will escape from open connections&r, lowering the pressure in the system. Right-clicking a connection with any Wrench will shut that connection.

ftbuniversity.pressuregaugemod.subtitle=制作一个 Pressure Gauge Tube Module
ftbuniversity.pressuregaugemod.desc1=The &bPressure Gauge Tube Module&r can be placed on a Pressure Tube to &6display its pressure visually&r, and will emit a redstone signal based on that.
ftbuniversity.pressuregaugemod.desc2=Using an Advanced PCB on it will upgrade it, allowing you to change the redstone signal strength emitted based on the pressure.

ftbuniversity.redscreenmod.subtitle=制作一个 Redstone Screen Module
ftbuniversity.redscreenmod.desc1=&bRedstone Screen Modules&r will &6transport a redstone signal&r, carried along the Pressure Tubes. &6Use a Wrench to toggle between input and output.&r
ftbuniversity.redscreenmod.desc2=You can have &616 channels&r, set by using a dye on the Modules.
ftbuniversity.redscreenmod.desc3=Installing an Advanced PCB on the output end will give it several logic operations it can use, instead of just input-output. Each operation will show its logic at the bottom of the GUI.

ftbuniversity.safetytubemod.subtitle=制作一个 Safety Tube Module
ftbuniversity.safetytubemod.desc1=The &bSafety Tube Module&r can be placed on a Presure Tube to &6release pressured air when it gets dangerously high&r.
ftbuniversity.safetytubemod.desc2=It defaults to releasing air &6when it reaches 7.5 bar&r, though an Advanced PCB can be used on it to allow you to change the threshold.

ftbuniversity.pcsecurityup.title=The Most Important Thing Ever
ftbuniversity.pcsecurityup.subtitle=制作一个 Security Upgrade
ftbuniversity.pcsecurityup.desc1=The &bSecurity Upgrade&r can be installed onto most machines to &6make them act like a Safety Tube Module&r, releasing pressured air when it reaches critical amounts.
ftbuniversity.pcsecurityup.desc2=Basically, install these on everything you ever make.

ftbuniversity.regulatormod.subtitle=制作一个 Regulator Tube Module
ftbuniversity.regulatormod.desc1=The &bRegulator Tube Module&r allows you to &6limit the air that flows through it&r. Air will only flow from the input (the wide end) to the output (the thin end) &6when the output's pressure is below a threshold&r.
ftbuniversity.regulatormod.desc2=The Regulator Tube acts as a &6transformer&r, allowing you to have a high-pressure system convert into a low-power system.
ftbuniversity.regulatormod.desc3=The pressure threshold is set by the redstone signal strength given to it (&6see the PNC:R Manual&r). Installing an Advanced PCB onto it will allow you to manually set the exact threshold.

ftbuniversity.airgratemod.subtitle=制作一个 Air Grate Tube Module
ftbuniversity.airgratemod.desc1=The &bAir Grate Tube Module&r will use compressed air to &6move entities&r in its range (see the tooltip for details).
ftbuniversity.airgratemod.desc2=Positive air pressure will push, and negative air pressure (which requires a Vacuum Pump) will pull.
ftbuniversity.airgratemod.desc3=Using an Advanced PCB on it will upgrade it, allowing you to set what entities are affected.
ftbuniversity.airgratemod.desc4=The Air Grate can also be used to &6cool Heat Sinks&r that are within a 3x3x3 cube in front of it.

ftbuniversity.aircompressor.title=What's the Matter Compressor?
ftbuniversity.aircompressor.subtitle=制作一个 Air Compressor
ftbuniversity.aircompressor.desc1=The &bAir Compressor&r burns solid furnace fuel to &6generate compressed air&r.
ftbuniversity.aircompressor.desc2=The left tabs can be expanded to see information about the machine, set how redstone effects it, and see information about upgrades.

ftbuniversity.liquidcompressor.title=Note: Does Not Compress Liquids
ftbuniversity.liquidcompressor.subtitle=制作一个 Liquid Compressor
ftbuniversity.liquidcompressor.desc1=The &bLiquid Compressor&r uses fluid fuel to &6generate compressed air&r, but otherwise functions identical to the Air Compressor.
ftbuniversity.liquidcompressor.desc2=The bottom left tab will show you what fuels are available, and how much compressed air they create.

ftbuniversity.thermalcompressor.subtitle=制作一个 Thermal Compressor
ftbuniversity.thermalcompressor.desc1=The &bThermal Compressor&r generates compressed air based on the &6temperature difference across opposite horizontal sides&r. The bigger the difference, the more pressure.
ftbuniversity.thermalcompressor.desc2=Over time, the hot block will cool down, and the cold block will heat up.
ftbuniversity.thermalcompressor.desc3=The Thermal Compressor isn't exactly the most useful machine, but it's fairly good for some edge-cases. &6Read the PNC:R Manual&r for more details.

ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.title=Developer Art Chamber
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.subtitle=Construct a Pressure Chamber
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.desc1=The &bPressure Chamber&r is a multiblock machine that uses compressed air to craft items. With its large volume, it also works as a container of compressed air.
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.desc2=&6Read the PNC:R Manual to see how it's constructed.&r
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.desc3=&bPressure Chamber Interfaces&r are the only way to input or extract items. It grabs items on the I side and puts them out the O side, so you have to be standing inside the Chamber to make the output interface.
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.desc4=Items cannot be manually inserted or extracted, you &6have to use some form of automation&r (pipes etc). It is highly suggested to set a filter on the output Interface, so it doesn't just instantly pull out the ingredients.
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.desc5=1000mL of air is used up per item inserted/extracted.
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.desc6=Compressed Air is inserted through the &bPressure Chamber Valve&r.
ftbuniversity.pressurechamber.task=Any Pressure Chamber wall block

ftbuniversity.harvestdrone.subtitle=制作一个 Harvesting Drone
ftbuniversity.harvestdrone.desc1=The &bHarvesting Drone&r uses compressed air to &6harvest crops/trees&r in a 17x17x17 cube centered on the block it is clicked on.
ftbuniversity.harvestdrone.desc2=If the Drone is &6deployed on an inventory that &nonly&r&6 contains a Hoe&r, it will &6automatically replant saplings and seeds&r
ftbuniversity.harvestdrone.desc3=Harvesting drones are &cincapable of picking up items&r.
ftbuniversity.harvestdrone.desc4=Use any Wrench on the Drone to dismantle it.

ftbuniversity.pnrefinery.subtitle=制作一个 Refinery
ftbuniversity.pnrefinery.desc1=The &bRefinery&r uses an adjacent heat source to &6convert Oil into Diesel, Kerosene, Gasoline, and LPG&r. 
ftbuniversity.pnrefinery.desc2=You have to have &6multiple Refineries stacked on top of each other&r for it to function. The more stacked, the more fluids are crafted.
ftbuniversity.pnrefinery.desc3=At 4 Refineries, all 4 fluids are created.

ftbuniversity.vortextube.title=Hanrei Hannen
ftbuniversity.vortextube.subtitle=制作一个 Vortex Tube
ftbuniversity.vortextube.desc1=The &bVortex Tube&r uses compressed air to &6make one side hot and the other side cold&r.
ftbuniversity.vortextube.desc2=The higher the airflow, the more extreme the temperatures.

ftbuniversity.pnthermoprocplant.title=Easier to Pronounce Than It Looks
ftbuniversity.pnthermoprocplant.subtitle=制作一个 Thermopneumatic Processing Plant
ftbuniversity.pnthermoprocplant.desc1=The &bThermopneumatic Processing Plant&r uses heat and/or air pressure to either &6combine an item and a fluid&r or &6convert one fluid into another&r.
ftbuniversity.pnthermoprocplant.desc2=It's most often used to &6make Liquid Plastic&r.

ftbuniversity.pnspeed.subtitle=Make Speed Upgrades
ftbuniversity.pnspeed.desc=&bSpeed Upgrades&r can go in pretty much anything to make them faster.

ftbuniversity.plasticmixer.title=Plastic Beach
ftbuniversity.plasticmixer.subtitle=制作一个 Plastic Mixer
ftbuniversity.plasticmixer.desc1=The &bPlastic Mixer&r is used to &6combine Liquid Plastic and dye into solid Plastic&r, to use in crafting recipes.
ftbuniversity.plasticmixer.desc2=Give it Liquid Plastic and some red, green, and blue dyes, then &6open the Item Selection tab on the right to choose what color Plastic to craft&r.
ftbuniversity.plasticmixer.desc3=You can also melt solid Plastic back into Liquid Plastic, though this requires heat.

ftbuniversity.pcharstat.subtitle=制作一个 Charging Station
ftbuniversity.pcharstat.desc1=The &bCharging Station&r allows you to &6fill items with compressed air&r, allowing them to work.
ftbuniversity.pcharstat.desc2=It will only fill items to have equal pressure that the Charging Station itself has.

ftbuniversity.chargemod.subtitle=制作一个 Charging Module
ftbuniversity.chargemod.desc=The &bCharging Module&r can be placed on a Pressure Tube and it will charge all items in the inventory it is facing.

ftbuniversity.pnaircan.title=Canned Air
ftbuniversity.pnaircan.subtitle=制作一个 Air Canister
ftbuniversity.pnaircan.desc1=The &bAir Canister&r is essentially PneumaticCraft's battery, as it &6stores compressed air&r.
ftbuniversity.pnaircan.desc2=However, its main use is to be crafted into tools. Any air in the Air Can will be kept in the tool it is crafted into.
ftbuniversity.pnaircan.desc3=However however, putting a high-pressure Air Canister into a low-pressure Charging Station will &6discharge the Canister, emptying into the system&r.

ftbuniversity.vortexcannon.title=FWOOF
ftbuniversity.vortexcannon.subtitle=制作一个 Vortex Cannon
ftbuniversity.vortexcannon.desc1=The &bVortex Cannon&r &6shoots a burst of air&r when used.
ftbuniversity.vortexcannon.desc2=Air bursts &6push entities&r, &6uproot crops&r, &6break leaves&r, and &6shears sheep&r.
ftbuniversity.vortexcannon.desc3=&6The higher the air pressure, the more effective it is.&r

ftbuniversity.camoapp.title=Camouflage is Very Hard to Spell
ftbuniversity.camoapp.subtitle=制作一个 Camouflage Applicator
ftbuniversity.camoapp.desc1=The &bCamouflage Applicator&r can &6make camouflageable blocks look like other blocks&r.
ftbuniversity.camoapp.desc2=Sneak right-click the Applicator on a block (like Grass or Stone), then click on a any camouflageable block (which &6will be highlighted when holding the applicator&r) to camouflage it.

ftbuniversity.amadron.title=Drone Delivery
ftbuniversity.amadron.subtitle=制作一个 Amadron Tablet
ftbuniversity.amadron.desc1=The &bAmadron Tablet&r allows you to &6trade Emeralds for certain items/fluids&r.
ftbuniversity.amadron.desc2=Sneak right-click the Tablet on an inventory to set it as the location for pickup/dropoff of items, or a tank for fluids.
ftbuniversity.amadron.desc3=Open the Tablet's GUI to select a trade. Click a trade, and a Drone will come pick up the item left of the arrow, and then another will drop off the item to the right.
ftbuniversity.amadron.desc4=Players can also create their own trade offers in the &6Custom Trades&r button. Using a &6GPS Tool&r, the player can set a block to be the source for what they're selling, and another block for the destination for what they're buying.

ftbuniversity.minigun.title=BRRRT
ftbuniversity.minigun.subtitle=制作一个 Minigun
ftbuniversity.minigun.desc1=The &bMinigun&r will shoot &bMinigun Ammo&r using compressed air by holding right-click.
ftbuniversity.minigun.desc2=Sneak click the Minigun to insert up to 4 Minigun Ammo boxes. &6Minigun Ammo can be combined with a potion (though it only has a chance of working), or upgraded into other types (Incendiary, Explosive, Freezing, etc).&r
ftbuniversity.minigun.desc3=In the Charging Station, you can &6install several upgrades to the Minigun&r.

ftbuniversity.pcb.title=PCB
ftbuniversity.pcb.subtitle=Go through all the steps to 制作一个 PCB
ftbuniversity.pcb.desc1=First, 制作一个 &bEmpty PCB&r in the Pressure Chamber.
ftbuniversity.pcb.desc2=To make it into an &bAssembled PCB&r, &6throw it in some &bEtching Acid&r.
ftbuniversity.pcb.desc3=A fresh Empty PCB has virtually no chance of successfully assembling. Put it in a &bUV Light Box&r to increase the chances.
ftbuniversity.pcb.desc4=Finally, craft it with some Transistors and Capacitors to 制作一个 &bPrinted Circuit Board&r, which is used in crafting recipes.

ftbuniversity.modulardrone.title=Modular Drones
ftbuniversity.modulardrone.subtitle=Program a Drone
ftbuniversity.modulardrone.desc1=&bDrones&r can be programmed, allowing them to automatically do all sorts of things.
ftbuniversity.modulardrone.desc2=Drones are programmed in the &bProgrammer&r. Programming a Drone works kind of like the program Scratch, if you've ever used that.
ftbuniversity.modulardrone.desc3=Program code uses Widgets, which you can drag from the right of the GUI.
ftbuniversity.modulardrone.desc4=Widgets have pegs sticking out the bottom; putting another widget's top slot over it will connect them.
ftbuniversity.modulardrone.desc5=This quest will give you an example of a programmed Drone; &6put the Drone in the top right slot and click the ← button to see how it works.

ftbuniversity.pneucompat.title=Mod Compatibility!
ftbuniversity.pneucompat.subtitle=Make the RF/EU compatible machines
ftbuniversity.pneucompat.desc1=The &bPneumatic Dynamo&r and &bPneumatic Generator&r use compressed air to &6generate RF or EU respectively&r.
ftbuniversity.pneucompat.desc2=The &bFlux Compressor&r and &bElectric Compressor&r generate compressed air &6using RF and EU respectively&r.
ftbuniversity.pneucompat.task1=Air to Energy
ftbuniversity.pneucompat.task2=Energy to Air

ftbuniversity.pneumaticarmor.title=PneumaticMan
ftbuniversity.pneumaticarmor.subtitle=Make Pneumatic Armor
ftbuniversity.pneumaticarmor.desc1=&bPneumatic armor&r, though it has a fairly low defense, &6can be upgraded&r to give it &6more armor&6 or &6extra functionality&r (speed, flight, night vision, etc).
ftbuniversity.pneumaticarmor.desc2=&6Read the PNC:R Manual&r to see what upgrades can be installed on each part.
ftbuniversity.pneumaticarmor.desc3=Pneumatic armor &cdoes not have infinite durability&r, unlike some other powered armors.

ftbuniversity.transfergadget.title=Flat Transfer Gadget
ftbuniversity.transfergadget.subtitle=制作一个 Transfer Gadget
ftbuniversity.transfergadget.desc1=the &bTransfer Gadget&r can be placed between two adjacent inventories, and will &6move items/fluids from the blue side to the orange side&r.
ftbuniversity.transfergadget.desc2=It &6works every 2 seconds&r, moving 1 item or 100mB of fluid.
ftbuniversity.transfergadget.desc3=Click it with a Logistics Configurator to mirror it, or sneak click to dismantle.

ftbuniversity.spawneragitator.subtitle=制作一个 Spawner Agitator
ftbuniversity.spawneragitator.desc1=The &bSpawner Agitator&r can be placed on a vanilla Monster Spawner to &6make it work when no player is near&r, as well as preventing the spawned mobs from despawning.
ftbuniversity.spawneragitator.desc2=Sneak click it with a Logistics Configurator to dismantle it.

ftbuniversity.passemblyline.title=Assembly Line
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.subtitle=制作一个 Assembly Line
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.desc1=&bAssembly lines&r are multiblock machines that allow for certain crafting recipes. All parts of the assembly line must touch.
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.desc2=The &bAssembly Controller&r is where air is input, and contains the Assembly Program.
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.desc3=The &bAssembly Platform&r must be the center point of the assembly line. Every other block must be able to reach it.
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.desc4=&bAssembly IO Units&r control input and output of the assembly line. They must be able to reach an inventory and the Assembly Platform. They can reach anything within a 3x3 area centered on itself. Click it with a Wrench to toggle between input and output mode.
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.desc5=The &bAssembly Drill&r and &bAssembly Laser&r must be placed directly adjacent to the Assembly Platform.
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.desc6=&bAssembly Programs&r are insert into the Assembly Controller, and allow for specific recipes. The first two have separate recipes, but can be combined.
ftbuniversity.passemblyline.task=Assembly Programs

ftbuniversity.advtubes.subtitle=制作一个dvanced Pressure Tubes
ftbuniversity.advtubes.desc=&bAdvanced Pressure Tubes&r can handle &64 times the volume&r and &6up to 25.0 bar&r.

ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.title=Logistic &mPipes&r Drones
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.subtitle=Set up a Logistic System
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc1=A &bLogistics System&r allows you to automatically manage the transfer of items and fluids between destinations via Drones.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc2=&bLogistic Drones&r are what carry out the transfer of items. Simply place one down anywhere near the system. They will automatically move to inventories in the system, and automatically fill up at Charging Stations.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc3=&bLogistic Frames&r can be &6placed on any inventory or tank&r to add them to the system, functioning in different ways depending on which Frame it is.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc4=• The &bPassive Provider&r will allow anything in the system to pull from its contents, but will not push anything.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc5=• The &bActive Provider&r will try to empty the inventory it is placed on, pushing its contents to anything in the system that will accept it.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc6=• The &bStorage&r will accept from Active Providers, and can be pulled from by a Requester.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc7=• The &bDefault Storage&r works identical to regular Storage, except it has a lower priority.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc8=• The &bRequester&r will try to pull items/fluids set by its whitelist from Providers or Storage. It will only request the specified amount of each item as well.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.desc9=The &bLogistic Configurator&r can be used on any Logistic Frame to edit them, allowing you to set a whitelist.
ftbuniversity.logisticdrones.task=Any Logistic Frame

###EnderIO
ftbuniversity.eiochap.title=Ender IO

ftbuniversity.grainsofinfinity.title=To Infinity, and Below!
ftbuniversity.grainsofinfinity.subtitle=Get Grains of Infinity
ftbuniversity.grainsofinfinity.desc1=The most-used resource in Ender IO is &bGrains of Infinity&r.
ftbuniversity.grainsofinfinity.desc2=You can get Grains of Infinity by &6lighting Bedrock on fire&r, though it doesn't have a 100%% chance of dropping.
ftbuniversity.grainsofinfinity.desc3=You can easily automate it using a &6Dispenser with Flint and Steel&r.

ftbuniversity.simplechassis.subtitle=制作一个 Simple Machine Chassis
ftbuniversity.simplechassis.desc1=The &bSimple Machine Chassis&r is required in the crafting recipe for all Simple machines.
ftbuniversity.simplechassis.desc2=&c&nDo not feel obligated to craft every Simple machine&r. If you craft a higher-tier machine, &6it will automatically complete the lower-tier version's quests&r.
ftbuniversity.simplechassis.desc3=The only machines you &oneed&r to progress are the Simple SAG Mill and Simple Alloy Smelter.

ftbuniversity.simplestirling.subtitle=制作一个 Simple Stirling Generator
ftbuniversity.simplestirling.desc1=The &bSimple Stirling Generator&r makes RF using Furnace fuel. You can hover over an item while in its GUI to see how much RF it makes.
ftbuniversity.simplestirling.desc2=&nTechnically&r, they call it µI, but it's the same thing.

ftbuniversity.simplefurnace.title=Burn! Burn People!
ftbuniversity.simplefurnace.subtitle=制作一个 Simple Powered Furnace
ftbuniversity.simplefurnace.desc=The &bSimple Powered Furnace&r uses RF to smelt items.

ftbuniversity.simplealloy.title=Alloy Ally
ftbuniversity.simplealloy.subtitle=制作一个 Simple Alloy Smelter
ftbuniversity.simplealloy.desc=The &bSimple Alloy Smelter&r uses RF to combine metals into alloys.

ftbuniversity.simplesag.title=SWAG Mill
ftbuniversity.simplesag.subtitle=制作一个 Simple SAG Mill
ftbuniversity.simplesag.desc1=The &bSimple SAG Mill&r uses RF to crush items.
ftbuniversity.simplesag.desc2=Click the Paper button to see what can be crushed.
ftbuniversity.simplesag.rewards=Ore Dusts

ftbuniversity.simplecharger.title=Cha-Charger
ftbuniversity.simplecharger.subtitle=制作一个 Simple Wired Charger
ftbuniversity.simplecharger.desc=The &bSimple Wired Charger&r will charge items inserted into it with RF.

ftbuniversity.simplecrafter.subtitle=制作一个 Simple Crafter
ftbuniversity.simplecrafter.desc1=The &bSimple Crafter&r uses RF to automatically craft items.
ftbuniversity.simplecrafter.desc2=Set the recipe on the right, and then input items will go into the corresponding slots on the right.

ftbuniversity.capitems.title=Capacitors
ftbuniversity.capitems.subtitle=制作一个y Capacitor
ftbuniversity.capitems.desc1=&bCapacitors&r must be installed onto machines above Simple-tier for them to function.
ftbuniversity.capitems.desc2=Capacitors come in &6several tiers&r. Normally the order might not be obvious, but the mod &eLoot Capacitor Tooltips&r also adds tooltips showing the power of each.
ftbuniversity.capitems.desc3=&6Capacitors of higher tier work faster and store more RF.&r
ftbuniversity.capitems.desc4=Several of these Capacitors do not come default with Ender IO, and are actually from the addon mod &eEnder IO Endergy&r. They use the same mod id, so we've added tooltips to specify.
ftbuniversity.capitems.desc5=You may also find &bLoot Capacitors&r in dungeon chests. These give &6bonuses to specific machines&r. Normally you pretty much have to guess, but the mod &eLoot Capacitor Tooltips&r just puts it into the tooltip.
ftbuniversity.capitems.task=Any Capacitor

ftbuniversity.induschass.subtitle=制作一个 Industrial Machine Chassis
ftbuniversity.induschass.desc1=&bIndustrial Machine Chassis&r are used in the crafting recipes of normal-tier machines.
ftbuniversity.induschass.desc2=Again, you do not have to craft every machine in this tier; completing the Enhanced-tier quests will also complete these.
ftbuniversity.induschass.desc3=As of this tier, &6need to have Capacitors installed&r in the bottom left. See the Capacitor quest at the top for details.

ftbuniversity.stirlinggen.title=Sterling Generator
ftbuniversity.stirlinggen.subtitle=制作一个 Stirling Generator
ftbuniversity.stirlinggen.desc1=The &bStirling Generator&r uses furnace fuel to generate RF.
ftbuniversity.stirlinggen.desc2=The higher tier Capacitor installed, the more RF is generated.
ftbuniversity.stirlinggen.reward=Auto-complete Simple Stirling Generator quest

ftbuniversity.combustiongenerator.title=Sparky Sparky Boom Man
ftbuniversity.combustiongenerator.subtitle=制作一个 Combustion Generator
ftbuniversity.combustiongenerator.desc1=The &bCombustion Generator&r generates RF from &6fluid fuel and coolant&r.
ftbuniversity.combustiongenerator.desc2=See its uses in JEI for how much energy different combinations generate.

ftbuniversity.alloysmelter.title=Mix and Match
ftbuniversity.alloysmelter.subtitle=制作一个 Alloy Smelter
ftbuniversity.alloysmelter.desc1=The &bAlloy Smelter&r has all alloy and furnace recipes.
ftbuniversity.alloysmelter.desc2=The &6Furnace Mode&r button can toggle between using all recipes, using only furnace recipes, and using only alloy recipes.
ftbuniversity.alloysmelter.reward1=Auto-complete Simple Powered Furnace quest
ftbuniversity.alloysmelter.reward2=Auto-complete Simple Alloy Smelter quest

ftbuniversity.sagmill.title=Semi-Autogenous Grinding
ftbuniversity.sagmill.subtitle=制作一个 SAG Mill
ftbuniversity.sagmill.desc1=The &bSAG Mill&r uses RF to crush items.
ftbuniversity.sagmill.desc2=What separates this from the Simple SAG Mill is that you can insert &bGrinding Balls&r, which give a chance to give more drops and use less energy. See their thumbnails for information.
ftbuniversity.sagmill.task=Grinding Balls
ftbuniversity.sagmill.reward=Auto-complete Simple SAG Mill quest

ftbuniversity.wiredcharger.subtitle=制作一个 Wired Charger
ftbuniversity.wiredcharger.desc1=The &bWired Charger&r will charge items inserted into it using RF.
ftbuniversity.wiredcharger.desc2=Its charging speed is entirely dependant on the maximum RF of the item being charged, not the Capacitor.
ftbuniversity.wiredcharger.reward=Auto-complete Simple Wired Charger quest

ftbuniversity.eiocrafter.subtitle=制作一个 Crafter
ftbuniversity.eiocrafter.desc1=The &bCrafter&r uses RF to automatically craft items.
ftbuniversity.eiocrafter.desc2=Unlike the Simple Crafter, you can &6set if each slot can have only 1 item or an entire stack&r.
ftbuniversity.eiocrafter.reward=Auto-complete Simple Crafter quest

ftbuniversity.thevat.title=Not Just Any Vat
ftbuniversity.thevat.subtitle=Make The Vat
ftbuniversity.thevat.desc1=The &bThe Vat&r is used to brew certain fluids.
ftbuniversity.thevat.desc2=The Vat has one input fluid and 2 input items, and 1 fluid result. Most recipes can accept multiple items, some of which result in more of the resultant fluid.

ftbuniversity.powermonitor.subtitle=制作一个 Power Monitor
ftbuniversity.powermonitor.desc1=The &bPower Monitor&r can be connected to a Conduit network to its statistics.
ftbuniversity.powermonitor.desc2=It will show RF in Conduits, Capacitor Banks, and connected machines, and will also so the average RF/t input and output.
ftbuniversity.powermonitor.desc3=You can also set it to output a signal when RF storage is between two values.

ftbuniversity.graphpower.subtitle=制作一个 Graphical Power Monitor
ftbuniversity.graphpower.desc1=The &bGraphical Power Monitor&r has all the same functionality as the Power Monitor.
ftbuniversity.graphpower.desc2=However, it also has a graph of system energy over time on a logarithmic scale.

ftbuniversity.enhancedchassis.title=Chad Machines
ftbuniversity.enhancedchassis.subtitle=制作一个 Enhanced Machine Chassis
ftbuniversity.enhancedchassis.desc1=The &bEnhanced Machine Chassis&r are used in the recipes of Enhanced-tier machines.
ftbuniversity.enhancedchassis.desc2=Enhanced machines are generally faster. Also taller, though that doesn't really matter.

ftbuniversity.enhancedcombustion.subtitle=制作一个 Enhanced Combustion Generator
ftbuniversity.enhancedcombustion.desc=The &bEnhanced Combustion Generator&r makes &6twice as much RF&r as the Combustion Generator.
ftbuniversity.enhancedcombustion.reward=Auto-complete Combustion Generator quest

ftbuniversity.enhancedalloysmelt.subtitle=制作一个 Enhanced Alloy Smelter
ftbuniversity.enhancedalloysmelt.desc=The &bEnhanced Alloy Smelter&r is &6twice as fast&r as the Alloy Smelter.
ftbuniversity.enhancedalloysmelt.reward=Auto-complete Alloy Smelter quest

ftbuniversity.enhancedsag.subtitle=制作一个 Enhanced SAG Mill
ftbuniversity.enhancedsag.desc=The &bEnhanced SAG Mill&r is &6twice as fast&r as the SAG Mill.
ftbuniversity.enhancedsag.reward=Auto-complete SAG Mill quest

ftbuniversity.enhancedvat.subtitle=Make The Enhanced Vat
ftbuniversity.enhancedvat.desc=&bThe Enhanced Vat&r is &6twice as fast&r as The Vat.
ftbuniversity.enhancedvat.reward=Auto-complete The Vat quest

ftbuniversity.enhancedcharger.subtitle=制作一个 Enhanced Wired Charger
ftbuniversity.enhancedcharger.desc=The &bEnhanced Wired Charger&r has a &6much larger energy buffer&r, allowing it to more easily charge items that can store more RF.
ftbuniversity.enhancedcharger.reward=Auto-complete Wired Charger quest

ftbuniversity.soulchassis.subtitle=制作一个 Soul Machine Chassis
ftbuniversity.soulchassis.desc1=The &bSoul Machine Chassis&r are used in the recipes of most mob-centric machines.
ftbuniversity.soulchassis.desc2=It is not an upgrade to normal machines, it is specifically for certain machines.

ftbuniversity.slicesplice.title=Hack'N'Slash
ftbuniversity.slicesplice.subtitle=制作一个 Slice'N'Splice
ftbuniversity.slicesplice.desc1=The &bSlice'N'Splice&r basically &6infuses mob-essence to create items&r.
ftbuniversity.slicesplice.desc2=To run, it &6needs an Axe and Shears&r in its inventory.

ftbuniversity.soulbinder.subtitle=制作一个 Soul Binder
ftbuniversity.soulbinder.desc=The &bSoul Binder&r allows you to &6combine an item with a filled Soul Vial&r to create something new.

ftbuniversity.eioglass.title=Quite Nice
ftbuniversity.eioglass.subtitle=Make the permeable Quite Clear Glasses
ftbuniversity.eioglass.desc1=These versions of &bQuite Clear Glass&r can allow or disallow certain entities from passing through them.
ftbuniversity.eioglass.desc2=They come in normal, light-emitting, and light-blocking varients.
ftbuniversity.eioglass.task1=Player Glass
ftbuniversity.eioglass.task2=Monster Glass
ftbuniversity.eioglass.task3=Animal Glass

ftbuniversity.eiofarmer.subtitle=制作一个 Farming Station
ftbuniversity.eiofarmer.desc1=The &bFarming Station&r will automatically plant and harvest crops/trees in an area.
ftbuniversity.eiofarmer.desc2=To work, it obviously requires &6seeds/saplings&r and power, but also a &6Hoe&r. Tools in the Farming Station will use durability.
ftbuniversity.eiofarmer.desc3=If farming trees, it will also require an Axe. It will chop the entire tree at once, using a fairly large amount of durability. You can optionally give it Shears, if you want Leaves.
ftbuniversity.eiofarmer.desc4=The working area depends on the Capacitor. A tier 1 Capacitor will work a 7x7 area, while a tier 5 will work a 23x23 area.
ftbuniversity.eiofarmer.desc5=You can also give it some fertilizer (any mod's will work) to speed it up.

ftbuniversity.eiospawner.subtitle=制作一个 Powered Spawner
ftbuniversity.eiospawner.desc1=The &bPowered Spawner&r will use RF to spawn mobs.
ftbuniversity.eiospawner.desc2=&6Combine the Powered Spawner with a Broken Spawner&r to set it to the Spawner's mob. You can change the Spawner's mob using a Soul Binder.
ftbuniversity.eiospawner.desc3=You can also set the Powered Spawner to directly insert mobs into Soul Vials, instead of spawning in the world.

ftbuniversity.xpobel.subtitle=制作一个 Experience Obelisk
ftbuniversity.xpobel.desc1=The &bExperience Obelisk&r can store a nearly infinite amount of experience.
ftbuniversity.xpobel.desc2=In its GUI, you can move XP between it and yourself. You can also pump xp in and out as a fluid.

ftbuniversity.aversobel.subtitle=制作一个 Aversion Obelisk
ftbuniversity.aversobel.desc1=The &bAversion Obelisk&r will prevent specific mobs from spawning in its area using RF.
ftbuniversity.aversobel.desc2=In its GUI, give it up to 12 filled Soul Vials to choose which mobs to block.
ftbuniversity.aversobel.desc3=A tier 1 Capacitor gives it a working area of &665x65x65&r. A tier 5 Capacitor has a working area of &6&n385x385x385&r.

ftbuniversity.attrobel.subtitle=制作一个 Attractor Obelisk
ftbuniversity.attrobel.desc1=The &bAttractor Obelisk&r will make specific mobs in its area try to navigate to it using RF.
ftbuniversity.attrobel.desc2=In its GUI, give it up to 12 filled Soul Vials to choose which mobs to attract.
ftbuniversity.attrobel.desc3=A tier 1 Capacitor gives it a working area of &617x17x17&r. A tier 5 Capacitor has a working area of &6257x257x257&r.

ftbuniversity.inhibobel.subtitle=制作一个 Inhibitor Obelisk
ftbuniversity.inhibobel.desc1=The &bInhibitor Obelisk&r will prevent teleportation in its working area (though it only works on Endermen and thrown Ender Pearls) using RF.
ftbuniversity.inhibobel.desc2=A tier 1 Capacitor gives it a working area of &633x33x33&r. A tier 5 Capacitor has a working area of &6193x193x193&r.

ftbuniversity.weathobel.subtitle=制作一个 Weather Obelisk
ftbuniversity.weathobel.desc1=The &bWeather Obelisk&r changes the weather using a catalyst fluid attached to a Firework Rocket (and RF).
ftbuniversity.weathobel.desc2=See its uses in JEI to see what catalysts make what weathers.

ftbuniversity.eiosolar.title=Solar Energy
ftbuniversity.eiosolar.subtitle=制作一个 Photovoltaic Cell
ftbuniversity.eiosolar.desc1=&bPhotovoltaic Cells&r are solar panels, generating energy when they have sunlight.
ftbuniversity.eiosolar.desc2=There are 4 tiers, each generating more than the last. See their tooltips for exact numbers.
ftbuniversity.eiosolar.desc3=Cells of the same type will connect. Power is output from the bottom.
ftbuniversity.eiosolar.task=Any Photovoltaic Cell

ftbuniversity.yetawrench.title=Yeta Nother Wrench
ftbuniversity.yetawrench.subtitle=制作一个 Yeta Wrench
ftbuniversity.yetawrench.desc1=The &bYeta Wrench&r is Ender IO's way of configuring Conduits. Sneak right-clicking will instantly break any EIO machine.
ftbuniversity.yetawrench.desc2=Scroll while sneaking to 制作一个ll but one Conduit type invisible.
ftbuniversity.yetawrench.desc3=See its tooltip for more information.

ftbuniversity.eiomagnet.title=Apparently Literally Everything is Magnetic
ftbuniversity.eiomagnet.subtitle=制作一个 Electromagnet
ftbuniversity.eiomagnet.desc1=The &bElectromagnet&r will pull items towards you while on, using RF.
ftbuniversity.eiomagnet.desc2=Sneak right-click it to toggle it on or off. It must be in your hotbar or bauble slots to function.

ftbuniversity.eiochargeritem.title=Portable Battery
ftbuniversity.eiochargeritem.subtitle=制作一个 Inventory Charger
ftbuniversity.eiochargeritem.desc1=&bInventory Chargers&r use RF to charge items in your inventory (though the Simple one only charges adjacent items).
ftbuniversity.eiochargeritem.desc2=For it to function, you have to &6install a Dark Steel Upgrade "Empowered"&r using a Dark Steel Anvil.
ftbuniversity.eiochargeritem.desc3=Right-click the Inventory Charger to turn it on or off.
ftbuniversity.eiochargeritem.task=Any Inventory Charger

ftbuniversity.xpvacuum.subtitle=制作一个 XP Vacuum
ftbuniversity.xpvacuum.desc1=The &bXP Vacuum&r, when activated, will pull nearby experience orbs towards itself, and then insert them into an adjacent tank.
ftbuniversity.xpvacuum.desc2=To activate it, &6click it with a Liquid XP Bucket&r.

ftbuniversity.vacuumchest.subtitle=制作一个 Vacuum Chest
ftbuniversity.vacuumchest.desc1=The &bVacuum Chest&r will pick up items in its range, inserting them into itself.
ftbuniversity.vacuumchest.desc2=You can set the range in its GUI, as well as insert a Filter for a whitelist/blacklist.

ftbuniversity.travelanchor.subtitle=制作一个 Travel Anchor
ftbuniversity.travelanchor.desc1=While standing on a &bTravel Anchor&r, you can teleport to any other Travel Anchor within 96 blocks, even without line of sight. Move between Travel Anchors by &6jumping or sneaking while while looking at the destination&r.
ftbuniversity.travelanchor.desc2=In its GUI, you can give it a name and insert any item, to make it easier to tell them apart.
ftbuniversity.travelanchor.desc3=You can also set it to &6Public&r (anyone can use it), &6Private&r (only you can use it), and &6Protected&r (give it a 5-item "passcode"). You can also toggle its &6visibility&r, setting it so you can leave it but not teleport to it.

ftbuniversity.soulvial.subtitle=制作一个 Soul Vial
ftbuniversity.soulvial.desc1=Using a &bSoul Vial&r on any mob will pick it up, filling the Vial. Using it again will place the mob back down.
ftbuniversity.soulvial.desc2=This can be used to move mobs, but certain filled Vials are also used in crafting recipes.

ftbuniversity.eiowirelesscharger.subtitle=制作一个 Wireless Charger
ftbuniversity.eiowirelesscharger.desc=The &bWireless Charger&r will charge items in players' inventories, as long as they are within a &633x33x33 area&r centered on it.

ftbuniversity.eioenchanter.subtitle=制作一个 Enchanter
ftbuniversity.eioenchanter.desc1=The &bEnchanter&r will use your experience, some Lapis Lazuli, and certain items to make Enchanted Books.
ftbuniversity.eioenchanter.desc2=See its uses in JEI to see what enchantments it can give, and what they cost.

ftbuniversity.darkanvil.subtitle=制作一个 Dark Steel Anvil
ftbuniversity.darkanvil.desc1=The &bDark Steel Anvil&r, in addition to having a higher durability&r, allows you to upgrade certain Ender IO items.
ftbuniversity.darkanvil.desc2=Place the upgradable item in the bottom right slot and it will show its possible upgrades. Simply insert them into the slots to install them, and remove to uninstall them.

ftbuniversity.eioantenna.title=More Wireless Charging
ftbuniversity.eioantenna.subtitle=制作一个 Wireless Charging Antenna
ftbuniversity.eioantenna.desc1=&bWireless Charging Antennas&r have a larger range than the normal Wireless Charger. Power them from the bottom.
ftbuniversity.eioantenna.desc2=The normal WCA has a working area of &649x49x49&r, and the Enhanced WCA has &6129x129x129&r.

ftbuniversity.paintingmachine.subtitle=制作一个 Painting Machine
ftbuniversity.paintingmachine.desc1=The &bPainting Machine&r allows you to change the textures of certain things to look like other blocks.
ftbuniversity.paintingmachine.desc2=Put the block that you want the texture of on the left, and place the block you want to paint on the right.
ftbuniversity.paintingmachine.desc3=This is especially useful for &bFacades&r. You can paint a Facade on then apply it to a Conduit to make it look like the painted block.
ftbuniversity.paintingmachine.task=Any Facade

ftbuniversity.staffoftraveling.title=Vwoop
ftbuniversity.staffoftraveling.subtitle=制作一个 Staff of Traveling
ftbuniversity.staffoftraveling.desc1=The &bStaff of Traveling&r uses RF to teleport you in the direction you're looking when used while sneaking.
ftbuniversity.staffoftraveling.desc2=You can also use it to teleport to a Travel Anchor within 256 blocks of you.

ftbuniversity.dimensionaltransceiver.title=Tesseract
ftbuniversity.dimensionaltransceiver.subtitle=制作一个 Dimensional Transceiver
ftbuniversity.dimensionaltransceiver.desc1=The &bDimensional Transciever&r can teleport RF, fluid, and items.
ftbuniversity.dimensionaltransceiver.desc2=You can &6set a channel&r for each thing to transfer. Set a name in the top text box, set if it's private or public, and then hit the + button.
ftbuniversity.dimensionaltransceiver.desc3=Then, choose the channel out of the list on the left, and set whether to send or receive on that channel.

ftbuniversity.killerjoe.title=Butcher Pete
ftbuniversity.killerjoe.subtitle=制作一个 Killer Joe
ftbuniversity.killerjoe.desc1=The &bKiller Joe&r will kill mobs in a 5x4x5 area in front of it.
ftbuniversity.killerjoe.desc2=It &6does not use RF&r; instead, it uses &6Nutrient Distillation&r.
ftbuniversity.killerjoe.desc3=It will use the weapon in its inventory to kill mobs, applying its enchantments and dealing durability damage.

ftbuniversity.darkarmor.title=Dark Armor
ftbuniversity.darkarmor.subtitle=Make Dark armor
ftbuniversity.darkarmor.desc1=&bDark armor&r is &6equivalent in protection to Diamond&r, but can have &6Dark Steel Upgrades&r installed.
ftbuniversity.darkarmor.desc2=These upgrades can make it use RF, give extra jumps, increase speed, enable Elytra-esque flight (or a Glider), and much more.
ftbuniversity.darkarmor.desc3=See the Upgrades quest for details.
ftbuniversity.darkarmor.task=Dark armor

ftbuniversity.darktools.title=Dark Tools
ftbuniversity.darktools.subtitle=Make Dark tools
ftbuniversity.darktools.desc1=&bDark Tools&r are roughly equivalent to Diamond, but can have Dark Steel Upgrades installed.
ftbuniversity.darktools.desc2=These upgrades can make tools use RF and have their drops teleport to your inventory, make pickaxes dig Dirt, and more.
ftbuniversity.darktools.desc3=See the Upgrades quest for details.
ftbuniversity.darktools.task=Dark tools

ftbuniversity.zombiegen.subtitle=制作一个 Zombie Generator
ftbuniversity.zombiegen.desc=The &bZombie Generator&r produces RF using Nutrient Distillation.

ftbuniversity.enderarmor.title=Ender Armor
ftbuniversity.enderarmor.subtitle=Make Ender armor
ftbuniversity.enderarmor.desc1=&bEnder armor&r has &61.5 the protection of Diamond&r, and can have Dark Steel Upgrades installed. It also stores &61.5 times more RF&r than Dark armor.
ftbuniversity.enderarmor.desc2=See the Upgrades quest for details.
ftbuniversity.enderarmor.task=Ender armor
ftbuniversity.enderarmor.reward=Auto-complete Dark armor quest

ftbuniversity.endertools.title=Ender Tools
ftbuniversity.endertools.subtitle=Make Ender tools
ftbuniversity.endertools.desc1=&bEnder tools&r are around a 1.5 times upgrade to their Dark equivalent. They also can have Dark Steel Upgrades installed.
ftbuniversity.endertools.desc2=See the Upgrades quest for details.
ftbuniversity.endertools.task=Ender tools
ftbuniversity.endertools.reward=Auto-complete Dark tools quest

ftbuniversity.frankgen.subtitle=制作一个 Frank'n'Zombie Generator
ftbuniversity.frankgen.desc=The &bFrank'n'Zombie Generator&r is a straight upgrade to the Zombie Generator, producing more RF.
ftbuniversity.frankgen.reward=Auto-complete Zombie Generator quest

ftbuniversity.stellararmor.title=Stellar Armor
ftbuniversity.stellararmor.subtitle=Make Stellar armor
ftbuniversity.stellararmor.desc1=&bStellar armor&r is about &62.75 times as protective as Diamond&r, and can have Dark Steel Upgrades installed.
ftbuniversity.stellararmor.desc2=See the Upgrades quest for details.
ftbuniversity.stellararmor.task=Stellar armor
ftbuniversity.stellararmor.reward=Auto-complete the Ender armor quest

ftbuniversity.stellartools.title=Stellar Tools
ftbuniversity.stellartools.subtitle=Make Stellar tools
ftbuniversity.stellartools.desc1=&bStellar tools&r are about &62.75 times as good all-around&r as their Dark equivalent. They can also have Dark Steel Upgrades installed.
ftbuniversity.stellartools.desc2=See the Upgrades quest for details.
ftbuniversity.stellartools.task=Stellar tools
ftbuniversity.stellartools.reward=Auto-complete the Ender tool quest

ftbuniversity.endergenerator.subtitle=制作一个 Ender Generator
ftbuniversity.endergenerator.desc=The &bEnder Generator&r generates RF using &6Dew of the Void&r.

ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.title=Upgrades
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.subtitle=制作一个 Dark Steel Upgrade
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.desc1=&bDark Steel Upgrades&r can be applied to Dark, Ender, and Stellar armor and tools.
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.desc2=Each upgrade does something different, which you can see in their tooltips. Some upgrades require other upgrades already be installed.
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.desc3=Upgrades &6must be activated&r before they are installed. To activate them, right-click them while you have enough experience levels.
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.desc4=&6See the Dark Anvil quest&r for upgrade installation instructions.
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.desc5=Some Upgrades might seem like a good idea (&mcough cough Explosive&r), but can be removed just as easily as they are installed simply by taking the item out.
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.task1=Universal Upgrades
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.task2=Armor Upgrades
ftbuniversity.eioupgrades.task3=Tool Upgrades

ftbuniversity.itemconduit.subtitle=Make Item Conduits
ftbuniversity.itemconduit.desc1=&bItem Conduits&r will teleport items from input inventories to output inventories.
ftbuniversity.itemconduit.desc2=Place Item Conduits along the path you want to travel, connecting all inventories you want to interact with.
ftbuniversity.itemconduit.desc3=Click an inventory connection to edit it, allowing you to enable/disable &6Insert&r and &6Extract&r individually.
ftbuniversity.itemconduit.desc4=You can also set a color channel for each, and give each an Item Filter.
ftbuniversity.itemconduit.desc5=You can put every kind of Conduit in the same block-space.

ftbuniversity.eiofilters.title=Filtering
ftbuniversity.eiofilters.subtitle=制作一个 Item Filter
ftbuniversity.eiofilters.desc1=&bItem Filters&r can be inserted into Inserting Item Conduits to set what is or isn't allowed to enter it.
ftbuniversity.eiofilters.desc2=You can sneak-click a Filter to open its GUI, if it has one.
ftbuniversity.eiofilters.desc3=There are many times of Item Filter. Their names should explain pretty adequately, and their tooltip will explain further if required.
ftbuniversity.eiofilters.task=Any Item Filter

ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.title=Fluid Conduit
ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.subtitle=Make Fluid Conduits
ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.desc1=&bFluid Conduits&r are used to transport fluids.
ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.desc2=There are several tiers; regular ones cannot move fluids upwards, Presurized ones can, and Ender ones simply teleport the fluid.
ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.desc3=Ender Fluid Conduits work pretty much exactly like Item Conduits, except for fluids.
ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.desc4=You can put every kind of Conduit in the same block-space.
ftbuniversity.fluidconduit.task=Any Fluid Conduit

ftbuniversity.eiofluidfilter.subtitle=制作一个 Fluid Filter
ftbuniversity.eiofluidfilter.desc=The &bFluid Filter&r has 5 slots for buckets, allowing you to create a whitelist/blacklist of up to 5 fluids.

ftbuniversity.energyconduit.title=Thrumming With Energy
ftbuniversity.energyconduit.subtitle=Make Energy Conduits
ftbuniversity.energyconduit.desc1=&bEnergy Conduits&r transfer RF.
ftbuniversity.energyconduit.desc2=Normally, there are only three tiers. However, the addon &eEnder IO Endergy&r 12 more tiers, for increasingly high RF transfer speeds.
ftbuniversity.energyconduit.desc3=You can enable/disable &6Insert&r and &6Extract&r individually per connection.
ftbuniversity.energyconduit.task=Any Energy Conduit

ftbuniversity.conduitprobe.subtitle=制作一个 Conduit Probe
ftbuniversity.conduitprobe.desc1=The &bConduit Probe&r has two modes: &6probe&r and &6copy/paste&r. Scroll while sneaking to move between them.
ftbuniversity.conduitprobe.desc2=In probe mode, you can click on Conduits to see information on them, such as energy in the system, redstone signal information, etc.
ftbuniversity.conduitprobe.desc3=In copy/paste mode, you can sneak click a connection to copy it, then click other connections to paste.

ftbuniversity.redstoneconduit.subtitle=Make Redstone Conduits
ftbuniversity.redstoneconduit.desc1=&bRedstone Conduits&r can carry 16 separate color-coded redstone signals.
ftbuniversity.redstoneconduit.desc2=You can insert a Redstone Filter to make them do complex functions.

ftbuniversity.eioredstonefilters.title=Redstone Filters
ftbuniversity.eioredstonefilters.subtitle=制作一个 Redstone Filter
ftbuniversity.eioredstonefilters.desc1=&bRedstone Filters&r are used to modulate redstone signals for complex functions.
ftbuniversity.eioredstonefilters.desc2=Aka, NOT Filters invert, OR Filters emit a strong signal if either input channels have a signal, AND Filters if both channels are on, etc.
ftbuniversity.eioredstonefilters.task=Any Redstone Filter

ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.title=RF Storage
ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.subtitle=制作一个 Capacitor Bank
ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.desc1=&bCapacitor Banks&r will store RF, with each tier storing a higher amount.
ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.desc2=Adjacent Capacitor Banks of the same tier will form a multiblock, pooling their storage.
ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.desc3=You can sneak click any face with an empty hand to change how it works. It can either show a gauge of how full it is, the RF/t being input out output, nothing, or disable interaction.
ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.desc4=You can break a Capacitor Bank and it will &6keep its RF&r.
ftbuniversity.capacitorbanks.task=Any Capacitor Bank

ftbuniversity.eiospeed.subtitle=制作一个 Extract Speed Upgrade
ftbuniversity.eiospeed.desc=&bExtract Speed Upgrades&r can be installed on Item Conduits and Ender Fluid Conduits to increase their extract speed.

ftbuniversity.eiotank.title=Fluid Storage
ftbuniversity.eiotank.subtitle=制作一个 Fluid Tank
ftbuniversity.eiotank.desc1=&bFluid Tanks&r can store 16,000mB of a single fluid. You can also fill or empty a fluid container in its GUI.
ftbuniversity.eiotank.desc2=The &bPressurized Fluid Tank&r is the same, but blast resistant and stores 32,000mB.
ftbuniversity.eiotank.task=Either Fluid Tank

###Mekanism
ftbuniversity.mekchap.title=Mekanism v9

ftbuniversity.mekic2.title=Not So Universal After All
ftbuniversity.mekic2.subtitle=Mekanism's EU support is disabled
ftbuniversity.mekic2.desc1=Normally, Mekanism can use both RF and EU. However, in order to not trivialize Industrial Craft, &cwe've disabled EU support&r in Mekanism.
ftbuniversity.mekic2.desc2=It is our opinion that, while energy conversion is an important feature of Mekanism, IC2 being its own system is more integral to the mod than energy conversion is to Mekanism.
ftbuniversity.mekic2.desc3=We do have the mod &eEnergy Converters&r, though it is locked behind the latest IC2 quests.

ftbuniversity.osmium.title=Ozzy Osmium
ftbuniversity.osmium.subtitle=Mine some Osmium
ftbuniversity.osmium.desc1=&bOsmium&r is an ore added by Mekanism, and is used in a lot of its recipes.
ftbuniversity.osmium.desc2=You can see where it generates in JEI.

ftbuniversity.mekheatgen.title=Burnables to Lava to Power
ftbuniversity.mekheatgen.subtitle=制作一个 Heat Generator
ftbuniversity.mekheatgen.desc1=The &bHeat Generator&r makes RF using one of two modes.
ftbuniversity.mekheatgen.desc2=In &6Active Power&r mode, inserting furnace fuels will burn them into Lava (somehow), and then use it to make RF.
ftbuniversity.mekheatgen.desc3=In &6Passive Power&r mode, placing Lava next to it will generate RF infinitely (though slowly).
ftbuniversity.mekheatgen.desc4=Power can only be output through the front (the flat side with the green square).

ftbuniversity.metallurgicinfuser.title=Alloys and Stuff
ftbuniversity.metallurgicinfuser.subtitle=制作一个 Metallurgic Infuser
ftbuniversity.metallurgicinfuser.desc1=The &bMetallurgic Infuser&r allows you to combine two items to create another.
ftbuniversity.metallurgicinfuser.desc2=The secondary material (dusts, usually) go into the far left slot, and have a buffer. The buffer can only store one material at a time.
ftbuniversity.metallurgicinfuser.desc3=Notably, it can be used to create allows like &6Bronze&r and &6Steel&r. Click the progress arrow to see all recipes.

ftbuniversity.meksolar.subtitle=制作一个 Solar Generator
ftbuniversity.meksolar.desc=The &bSolar Generator&r generates &617.6 RF/t&r when it can see the sun.

ftbuniversity.meksolar2.subtitle=制作一个 Advanced Solar Generator
ftbuniversity.meksolar2.desc=The &bAdvanced Solar Generator&r generates &6105.6 RF/t&r when it can see the sun.

ftbuniversity.mekwind.subtitle=制作一个 Wind Generator
ftbuniversity.mekwind.desc=The &bWind Generator&r produces RF based on its elevation. &6At y=200, it generates 384RF/t.&r

ftbuniversity.energycubes.subtitle=制作一个 Energy Cube
ftbuniversity.energycubes.desc1=&bEnergy Cubes&r come in four tiers, each storing more RF.
ftbuniversity.energycubes.desc2=See their tooltips for how much they store. The lowest stores &6800,000RF&r, and the highest stores &651,200,000RF&r.
ftbuniversity.energycubes.desc3=The top left button in their GUI allows you to set if each side is input or output.
ftbuniversity.energycubes.task=Energy Cubes

ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.title=Induction Matrix
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.subtitle=制作一个 Induction Matrix
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc1=The &bInduction Matrix&r is a multiblock machine that is used to &6store a massive amount of RF&r.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc2=The outermost walls must be made out of &bInduction Casing&r, making a rectangular prism that's, at largest, 18x18x18.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc3=Replace any of the walls with &bInduction Ports&r, where energy is inserted/extracted.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc4=The inside of the multiblock must have at least 1 &bInduction Provider&r and at least 1 &bInduction Cell&r. The only other acceptable block is air.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc5=Induction Providers increase the &6amount of RF you are able to insert/extract per tick&r. The more you have (and the higher tier you use), the more RF/t the Matrix as a whole can move. They can be placed anywhere inside.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc6=Induction Cells increase the &6amount of RF that is stored in the Matrix&r. The more you have (and the higher tier you use), the more RF is stored. They can be placed anywhere inside.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.desc7=Theoretically, an 18x18x18 Matrix with 1 Provider and 4095 Ultimate Induction Cells could around &6838,650,000,000,000 RF&r.
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.task1=Induction Providers
ftbuniversity.inductionmatrix.task2=Induction Cells

ftbuniversity.energizedsmelter.subtitle=制作一个 Energized Smelter
ftbuniversity.energizedsmelter.desc=The &bEnergized Smelter&r uses RF to smelt items.

# It took so much willpower to not be crass
ftbuniversity.seismic.title=Dirt Wiggler
ftbuniversity.seismic.subtitle=制作一个 Seismic Vibrator and 读取器
ftbuniversity.seismic.desc1=The &bSeismic Vibrator&r uses RF to allow the &bSeismic 读取器&r to work.
ftbuniversity.seismic.desc2=The Seismic 读取器 will show all blocks in a 1x1 column beneath the Vibrator, all the way down to Bedrock.

ftbuniversity.mekpump.subtitle=制作一个 Electric Pump
ftbuniversity.mekpump.desc1=The &bElectric Pump&r uses RF to pump fluids under it, inserting it into the container above. It will pull from all connected source blocks as well.
ftbuniversity.mekpump.desc2=Sources are not replaced with Stone like some mods do, so this might cause lag from all the 
ftbuniversity.mekpump.desc3=If pumping Water, it will not remove the source blocks.
ftbuniversity.mekpump.desc4=It can only accept power from the back.

ftbuniversity.chargepad.subtitle=制作一个 Chargepad
ftbuniversity.chargepad.desc=When RF is piped in through the back, standing on the &bChargepad&r will charge items in your inventory.

ftbuniversity.combiner.title=Ore Gen, Technically
ftbuniversity.combiner.subtitle=制作一个 Combiner
ftbuniversity.combiner.desc=The &bCombiner&r allows you to combine Cobblestone and ore dusts to create Ores.

ftbuniversity.precsaw.subtitle=制作一个 Precision Sawmill
ftbuniversity.precsaw.desc1=The &bPrecision Sawmill&r uses RF to process wooden items more efficiently, creating more Planks, Sticks, etc.
ftbuniversity.precsaw.desc2=It is also the &6only source of Sawdust&r.

ftbuniversity.cardboard.title=Hrngh, Colonel
ftbuniversity.cardboard.subtitle=制作一个 Cardboard Box
ftbuniversity.cardboard.desc1=The &bCardboard Box&r can be used on any block to seal it, allowing it to be broken, moved, and used again while sneaking to unseal it exactly as it was.
ftbuniversity.cardboard.desc2=This can be used in place of Silk Touch, but also can move tile entities like machines and spawners!

ftbuniversity.logsorter.title=Kchk
ftbuniversity.logsorter.subtitle=制作一个 Logistical Sorter
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc1=The &bLogistical Sorter&r uses filters to pull items out of inventories and send them out the other side, either into another inventory or pipes (generally Logistical Transporters). When placed, it automatically turns to extract from an adjacent inventory.
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc2=There are 4 filter types:
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc3=• &6Itemstack&r: insert an item to set it. You can also set the minimum required and max allowed to be moved at a time, which requires you click the [s] button to enable Size Mode.
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc4=• &6OreDict&r: type in an Ore Dictionary term to accept all that use it. So stuff like plankWood, blockGlass, etc. You can also use wildcards, so "ingot*" work. Enabling advanced tooltips will allow you to see an items oredict terms.
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc5=• &6Material&r: insert a placeable block and it will accept all items that are made of the same material. So, putting in wood will allow all wooden items.
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc6=• &6Mod ID&r: type in a mod id and it will accept all items from that mod.
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc7=The main screen also has buttons that allow you to toggle between stack/single-item modes, enabling round-robin mode (using Transporters), and if it ignores filters and just moves all items.
ftbuniversity.logsorter.desc8=You can also change the color tag, which is explained in the Logistical Transporter quest.

ftbuniversity.osmcomp.subtitle=制作一个 Osmium Compressor
ftbuniversity.osmcomp.desc1=The &bOsmium Compressor&r is used to &6infuse Osmium into Obsidian or Glowstone&r.
ftbuniversity.osmcomp.desc2=Put Osmium in the bottom slot, and then either Refined Obsidian Dust or Glowstone Dust to get a Refined Obsidian Ingot or Glowstone Ingot, respectively.

ftbuniversity.basicfactories.title=Parallel Production
ftbuniversity.basicfactories.subtitle=制作一个y Basic Factory
ftbuniversity.basicfactories.desc1=&bBasic Factories&r exist for most Mekanism machines, and function identically.
ftbuniversity.basicfactories.desc2=However, each Basic Factory has &63 inputs and outputs&r, allowing it work three stacks at once.
ftbuniversity.basicfactories.desc3=You can also enable &6Auto-sort&r, which will automatically split the input slots equally.
ftbuniversity.basicfactories.task=Basic Factories

ftbuniversity.advfactories.subtitle=制作一个y Advanced Factory
ftbuniversity.advfactories.desc=&bAdvanced Factories&r have &65 inputs and outputs&r.
ftbuniversity.advfactories.task=Advanced Factories

ftbuniversity.elitefactories.subtitle=制作一个y Elite Factory
ftbuniversity.elitefactories.desc=&bElite Factories&r have &67 inputs and outputs&r.
ftbuniversity.elitefactories.task=Elite Factories

ftbuniversity.formass.title=Sesquipedalian Compositator
ftbuniversity.formass.subtitle=制作一个 Formulaic Assemblicator
ftbuniversity.formass.desc1=The &bFormulaic Assemblicator&r allows you to automatically craft a single recipe using items piped into it.
ftbuniversity.formass.desc2=At the top, set the recipe. Then you can either set it to craft for as long as it has items in the slots, or craft only once.
ftbuniversity.formass.desc3=In order to craft infinitely using the storage slots, you have to insert a &bCrafting Formula&r and click the &6Encode Formula&r button.
ftbuniversity.formass.desc4=After that, you can click &6Auto-Mode&r to make it craft infinitely from its storage.

ftbuniversity.mekx2.title=Ore Doubling
ftbuniversity.mekx2.subtitle=Learn about Mekanism's ore processing
ftbuniversity.mekx2.desc1=Mekanism is unique among most mods in that it can process ores to get &6more than 2 times the normal amount of ingots&r.
ftbuniversity.mekx2.desc2=These quests will walk you through each step of the processing. To begin with, the quest below allows ore doubling.

ftbuniversity.enrichcenter.title=Aperature Science Enrichment Center
ftbuniversity.enrichcenter.subtitle=制作一个 Enrichment Chamber
ftbuniversity.enrichcenter.desc1=The &bEnrichment Chamber&r enriches items, cleaning them, compressing them, or extracting from them.
ftbuniversity.enrichcenter.desc2=This can be used to convert 1 ore into 2 dusts, as well as compress secondary materials for optimum use in the Metallurgic Infuser.

ftbuniversity.prc.title=PRC
ftbuniversity.prc.subtitle=制作一个 Pressurized Reaction Chamber
ftbuniversity.prc.desc1=The &bPressurized Reaction Chamber&r is used to combine a &6gas&r, &6fluid&r, and &6item&r to create something, usually &6Substrate&r or &6Ethylene&r.
ftbuniversity.prc.desc2=Items, energy, fluids, and gases can only be &6inserted into specific sides&r, remember. You can change these in the GUI; it has tabs for each.

ftbuniversity.gasburn.subtitle=制作一个 Gas-Burning Generator
ftbuniversity.gasburn.desc1=The &bGas-Burning Generator&r generates a fairly high amount of RF by burning certain gasses.
ftbuniversity.gasburn.desc2=A really good setup for this would be to &6grow Melon in a Garden Cloche&r, mash it into &6Bio Fuel&r, convert it to Substrate and Ethylene in the PRC, and then &6burn the Ethylene&r. This can run several Gas-Burning Generators in tandem.

ftbuniversity.mekx3.title=Ore Tripling
ftbuniversity.mekx3.subtitle=Learn how to triple ores
ftbuniversity.mekx3.desc=These quests will show how to triple your ore output.

ftbuniversity.electrosep.subtitle=制作一个 Electrolytic Separator
ftbuniversity.electrosep.desc1=The &bElectrolytic Separator&r takes one fluid and splits it into two &6gases&r (which are &nnot fluids&r).
ftbuniversity.electrosep.desc2=For &6ore doubling&r, you need to split Water into Hydrogen and &6Oxygen&r.
ftbuniversity.electrosep.desc3=For &6ore tripling&r, you need to split Brine into &6Chlorine&r and Sodium, as well as the &6Hydrogen&r from earlier.

ftbuniversity.purification.title=PURIFICATION! PURIFICATION!
ftbuniversity.purification.subtitle=制作一个 Purification Chamber
ftbuniversity.purification.desc1=The &bPurification Chamber&r uses Oxygen to &6convert ores into 3 ore Clumps&r.
ftbuniversity.purification.desc2=Oddly enough, you can use Flint as a source of Oxygen.

ftbuniversity.mekcrusher.subtitle=制作一个 Crusher
ftbuniversity.mekcrusher.desc1=The &bCrusher&r crushes items into dusts.
ftbuniversity.mekcrusher.desc2=In this case, you can crush Clumps into Dirty Dust, which you can then enrich and smelt into ingots.

ftbuniversity.mekx4.title=Ore Quadrupling
ftbuniversity.mekx4.subtitle=Learn how to quadruple ores
ftbuniversity.mekx4.desc=These quests will show you how to quadruple your ore output.

ftbuniversity.thermevap.title=Thermal Evaporation Plant
ftbuniversity.thermevap.subtitle=制作一个 Thermal Evaporation Plant
ftbuniversity.thermevap.desc1=The &bThermal Evaporation Plant&r is a multiblock machine that &6converts Water into Brine&r.
ftbuniversity.thermevap.desc2=Place a 4x4 platform of &bThermal Evaporation Blocks&r, and then build up the outer blocks by at least 2 layers using more TEBs, a &bThermal Evaporation Controller&r, and two &6Thermal Evaporation Valves&r.
ftbuniversity.thermevap.desc3=The minimum height is 3 blocks tall, but it can be increased up to 18 blocks tall to store more.
ftbuniversity.thermevap.desc4=The speed it works at is based on the temperature. It works much faster in hot biomes than cold ones.
ftbuniversity.thermevap.desc5=You can &6replace the top corners with Advanced Solar Generators&r to increase the temperature. The more Solar Generators, the higher the temperature.

ftbuniversity.cheminfuse.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Infuser
ftbuniversity.cheminfuse.desc1=The &bChemical Infuser&r combines/reacts two gases to create another.
ftbuniversity.cheminfuse.desc2=For ore quadrupling, you &6need Hydrogen Chloride, by combining Hydrogen and Chlorine&r (which you get from Brine)

ftbuniversity.cheminject.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Injection Chamber
ftbuniversity.cheminject.desc=The &bChemical Injection Chamber&r combines Hydrogen Chloride with ore to make &64 shards&r, which can each be purified into 1 Clump.

ftbuniversity.mekx5.title=Ore Quintupling
ftbuniversity.mekx5.subtitle=Learn how to quintuple ores
ftbuniversity.mekx5.desc=These quests will show you how to quintuple your ore output.

ftbuniversity.chemoxid.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Oxidizer
ftbuniversity.chemoxid.desc1=The &bChemical Oxidizer&r allows you to turn certain items into gases.
ftbuniversity.chemoxid.desc2=For the purposes of ore quintupling, you need to &6convert Sulfur to Sulfur Dioxide&r, which has to be combined with Oxygen in the Chemical Infuser to make &6Sulfer Trioxide&r.

ftbuniversity.rotarycondens.subtitle=制作一个 Rotary Condensator
ftbuniversity.rotarycondens.desc1=The &bRotary Condensator&r allows you to convert between the gas and fluid forms of certain chemicals.
ftbuniversity.rotarycondens.desc2=For the purposes of ore quintupling, you need to &6decondensentrate Water into Water Vapor&r, which has to be combined with Sulfur Trioxide in the Chemical Infuser to create &6Sulfuric Acid&r.

ftbuniversity.chemdiss.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Dissolution Chamber
ftbuniversity.chemdiss.desc=The &bChemical Dissolution Chamber&r allows you to combine ores with Sulfuric Acid to create a bucket of &6ore lurry&r.

ftbuniversity.chemwasher.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Washer
ftbuniversity.chemwasher.desc=The &bChemical Washer&r combines 5mB of Water with 1mB of ore Slurry to create 1mB of &6Clean ore Slurry&r.

ftbuniversity.chemcryst.subtitle=制作一个 Chemical Crystallizer
ftbuniversity.chemcryst.desc1=The &bChemical Crystallizer&r converts 200mB of Clean ore Slurry into an ore Crystal, which can be converted to a Shard, then Clump, then Dirty Dust, then Dust, then Ingot.
ftbuniversity.chemcryst.desc2=Recall that each ore is 1000mB, so you get &65 ingots total&r.

ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.title=Atomic Striker
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.subtitle=制作一个 Atomic Disassembler
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc1=The &bAtomic Disassembler&r works as a Pickaxe, Axe, Shovel, Hoe, and Scoop. It uses RF instead of durability, and cannot be enchanted.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc2=It has 6 modes. Swap between modes by sneak-right-clicking it.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc3=• &6Normal&r: As fast as a Diamond tool with Efficiency II. Hoes a 3x3 area.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc4=• &6Slow&r: As fast as a Diamond tool. Hoes a single block.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc5=• &6Fast&r: As fast as a Diamond tool with Efficiency V. Hoes a 5x5 area.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc6=• &6Vein&r: Mines all connected blocks of the same type, though it ignores Stone and other "normal" blocks.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc7=• &6Extended Vein Mining&r: Same as Vein, except it works on everything.
ftbuniversity.atomicdiss.desc8=• &6Off&r: Can't dig or hoe, but still deals damage.

ftbuniversity.robit.title=Become Human
ftbuniversity.robit.subtitle=制作一个 Robit
ftbuniversity.robit.desc1=The &bRobit&r is your friendly mechanical companion, pet, and ally!
ftbuniversity.robit.desc2=Place it down on a &6Chargepad&r to charge it. It will also teleport there when it runs out of power.
ftbuniversity.robit.desc3=When charged, right-click on it to open its GUI. There, you can toggle &6follow mode&r, teleport it back to its chargepad, toggle if it &6picks up items&r, and set its name.
ftbuniversity.robit.desc4=It also has a 3x3 crafting grid, 27 storage slots, a Furnace, and an Anvil. Move between these pages with the buttons on the right.
ftbuniversity.robit.desc5=Use a Configurator on it while sneaking to pick it up.

ftbuniversity.mekportal.title=Peletorter
ftbuniversity.mekportal.subtitle=制作一个 Teleporter
ftbuniversity.mekportal.desc1=The &bTeleporter&r is a multiblock that allows you to teleport between Teleporters on the same frequency.
ftbuniversity.mekportal.desc2=Place a Teleporter block, and 制作一个 hollow 4x3 of &bTeleporter Frames&r with the Teleporter centered on the bottom.
ftbuniversity.mekportal.desc3=Open the Teleporter block's GUI, optionally switch to Private mode if you only want yourself to be able to use it, and enter a name into the "Set" textbox to &6create a frequency&r.
ftbuniversity.mekportal.desc4=At other Teleporters, &6choose that frequency out of the list&r and click "Set."
ftbuniversity.mekportal.desc5=They really &6only work normally in pairs&r. If you add more, the additional ones all go to the first Teleporter. Entering the first Teleporter will always send you to the second Teleporter.

ftbuniversity.portableteleport.title=Porta-Port
ftbuniversity.portableteleport.subtitle=制作一个 Portable Teleporter
ftbuniversity.portableteleport.desc=The &bPortable Teleporter&r, when used, will allow you to pick a teleporter frequency, and then teleports you to the nearest Teleporter on it.

ftbuniversity.digitalminer.subtitle=制作一个 Digital Miner
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc1=The &bDigital Miner&r will search an area (default radius 10 blocks, max 32), scan it according to filters, and then mine those blocks and store their drops.
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc2=Click &6Config&r to set the filters, the radius, the minimum and maximum y levels it checks, and Inverse mode (making filters act as a blacklist).
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc3=Once your filters are set (I recommend an OreDict filter for "ore*"), click &6Start&r and let it run.
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc4=There are several more buttons on the main menu:
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc5=• &6Reset&r, which resets the block-mining position and allows you to change filters again.
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc6=• &6Auto-eject&r, which makes it automatically push items out the back.
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc7=• &6Silk touch&r, which applies a Silk Touch enchantment at the cost of additional RF.
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc8=• &6Auto-pull&r, which will replace mined blocks with a block from the inventory above itself.
ftbuniversity.digitalminer.desc9=You can also install upgrades in the top-right button menu.

ftbuniversity.quantumentangle.title=Verbose Tesseract
ftbuniversity.quantumentangle.subtitle=制作一个 Quantum Entangloporter
ftbuniversity.quantumentangle.desc1=The &bQuantum Entangloporter&r can be set a channel, and then will transport RF, fluids, gases, and items to other Entangloporters on the same channel.
ftbuniversity.quantumentangle.desc2=You have to set the input/output sides in the &6Side Config&r button menu.

ftbuniversity.mekspeed.subtitle=制作一个 Speed Upgrade
ftbuniversity.mekspeed.desc1=Up to 8 &bSpeed Upgrades&r can be installed to most Mekanism machines, making them work faster at the cost of more power.
ftbuniversity.mekspeed.desc2=Fully upgraded, a machine is &610x faster&r but uses &610x the RF&r.
ftbuniversity.mekspeed.desc3=Be warned: if you install so many Speed Upgrades that it &6requires more energy than can be stored&r, it &6won't work at all&r. You can fix this by installing Energy Upgrades.

ftbuniversity.mekenergy.subtitle=制作一个 Energy Upgrade
ftbuniversity.mekenergy.desc1=Up to 8 &bEnergy Upgrades&r can be installed to most Mekanism machines, making them use less and store more energy.
ftbuniversity.mekenergy.desc2=Fully upgraded, a machine &6uses 10x less&r and &6stores 10x more RF&r.

ftbuniversity.mekgas.subtitle=制作一个 Gas Upgrade
ftbuniversity.mekgas.desc=Up to 8 &bGas Upgrades&r can be installed to machines that use gas, lowering the amount they used.

ftbuniversity.mekmuffling.subtitle=制作一个 Muffling Upgrade
ftbuniversity.mekmuffling.desc=Up to 4 &bMuffling Upgrades&r can be installed to most Mekanism machines, making them less loud.

ftbuniversity.freerunners.title=Advanced Knee Replacement
ftbuniversity.freerunners.subtitle=Make Free Runners
ftbuniversity.freerunners.desc1=&bFree Runners&r, when charged and worn as boots, will allow you to &6walk up single blocks&r and &6negates all fall damage&r.
ftbuniversity.freerunners.desc2=However, it has no armor and thus gives no protection from attack damage.
ftbuniversity.freerunners.desc3=It only uses up charge when negating fall damage; higher falls drain more power.

ftbuniversity.mekscuba.title=Under the Sea
ftbuniversity.mekscuba.subtitle=制作一个 Gas Mask and Scuba Tank
ftbuniversity.mekscuba.desc1=The &bScuba Tank&r holds Oxygen gas, allowing you to &6breathe underwater&r while wearing the &bGas Mask&r.
ftbuniversity.mekscuba.desc2=You have to manually turn the Scuba Tank on and off using the &6Armor Mode Switch key&r (see Controls). If on, the Scuba Tank will use up Oxygen even if you are above water.

ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.title=Flammenwerfer
ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.subtitle=制作一个 Flamethrower
ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.desc1=The &bFlamethrower&r uses Hydrogen gas as fuel to shoot a stream of fire. The behavior of this stream depends on its mode:
ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.desc2=In &6Combat&r mode, it will damage mobs and set them on fire. It will also destroy drops, but will not light blocks on fire.
ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.desc3=In &6Heat&r mode, it still damages mobs but will smelt blocks and items.
ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.desc4=In &6Inferno&r mode, it will light blocks it touches on fire.
ftbuniversity.mekflamethrower.desc5=To swap between modes, hold shift and hit the &6Item Mode Switch&r key (see controls).

ftbuniversity.mekelecbow.subtitle=制作一个 Electric Bow
ftbuniversity.mekelecbow.desc1=The &bElectric Bow&r is simply a regular Bow that uses RF instead of durability. It cannot be enchanted.
ftbuniversity.mekelecbow.desc2=However, the &6Item Mode Switch&r key (see controls) can enable &6Fire Mode&r, which uses more RF to light arrows on fire.

ftbuniversity.mekjetpack1.subtitle=制作一个 Jetpack
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack1.desc1=The &bJetpack&r uses Hydrogen gas as fuel to allow you to fly upwards while holding jump.
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack1.desc2=It has three modes, which you can switch between using the &6Armor Mode Switch key&r (see Controls).
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack1.desc3=In &6Regular&r mode, holding space will make you rise, and releasing will make you fall.
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack1.desc4=In &6Hover&r mode, holding space will make you rise, and releasing will allow you to hover at that height (at a constant cost of Hydrogen). Sneaking will lower you down.
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack1.desc5=In &6Disabled&r mode, it does nothing other than look cool.

ftbuniversity.mekjetpack2.subtitle=制作一个 Armored Jetpack
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack2.desc1=The &bArmored Jetpack&r works identically to the Jetpack, except it gives &6slightly more protection than a Diamond Chestplate with Protection IV&r.
ftbuniversity.mekjetpack2.desc2=It can also be enchanted further.

ftbuniversity.universalcables.title="Universal" Cables
ftbuniversity.universalcables.subtitle=Make Universal Cables
ftbuniversity.universalcables.desc1=&bUniversal Cables&r are used to transfer RF. Normally, they can also move EU and convert between them, but we've disabled that.
ftbuniversity.universalcables.desc2=There are 4 tiers of Universal Cable, each moving and storing more than the last.
ftbuniversity.universalcables.desc3=You can upgrade Cables by clicking them (in tier order) with &6Enriched Alloy&r, &6Reinforced Alloy&r, and &6Atomic Alloy&r. This will upgrade up to 8 connected Cables at once.
ftbuniversity.universalcables.desc4=Cables use the MCMultiPart API, which means they can &6share a blockspace with Bits&r.
ftbuniversity.universalcables.task=Any Universal Cable

ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.title=Logistics Pipes™
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.subtitle=Make Logistical Transporters
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.desc1=&bLogistical Transporters&r are Mekanism's item pipes. Each tier moves items faster.
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.desc2=Sneak clicking a connection with a &6Configurator&r allows you to move between &6normal&r, &6push&r, &6pull&r, and &6none&r modes.
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.desc3=Items will try to go through the shortest possible path, &6prioritizing nearby destinations&r over farther away ones.
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.desc4=Sneak clicking the center of a pulling Logistical Transporter with a Configurator will change their color, &6painting items they extract&r, only allowing them to go through other painted &6Transporters of the same color&r.
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.desc5=You can upgrade Transporters by clicking them (in tier order) with &6Enriched Alloy&r, &6Reinforced Alloy&r, and &6Atomic Alloy&r. This will upgrade up to 8 connected Cables at once.
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.desc6=Logistical Transporters use the MCMultiPart API, which means they can &6share a blockspace with Bits&r.
ftbuniversity.logisticaltransporter.task=Any Logistical Transporter

ftbuniversity.mekspecialtransporters.title=Dense/Vacuum Itemducts
ftbuniversity.mekspecialtransporters.subtitle=制作一个 Restrictive/Diversion Transporter
ftbuniversity.mekspecialtransporters.desc1=The &bRestrictive Transporter&r adds 1000 to the path length, so destinations past it have a lower priority.
ftbuniversity.mekspecialtransporters.desc2=The &bDiversion Transporter&r removes 1000 from the path length, so destinations past it have a higher priority.

ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.title=The Bubbles Are Going!
ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.subtitle=Make Mechanical Pipes
ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.desc1=&bMechanical Pipes&r move fluids.
ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.desc2=Sneak clicking a connection with a &6Configurator&r allows you to move between &6normal&r, &6push&r, &6pull&r, and &6none&r modes.
ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.desc3=You can upgrade Pipes by clicking them (in tier order) with &6Enriched Alloy&r, &6Reinforced Alloy&r, and &6Atomic Alloy&r. This will upgrade up to 8 connected Cables at once.
ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.desc4=Mechanical Pipes use the MCMultiPart API, which means they can &6share a blockspace with Bits&r.
ftbuniversity.mechanicalpipes.task=Any Mechanical Pipe

ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.title=A Series of Tubes
ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.subtitle=Make Pressurized Tubes
ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.desc1=&bPressurized Tubes&r move gases. Higher tiers can move and store more.
ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.desc2=Sneak clicking a connection with a &6Configurator&r allows you to move between &6normal&r, &6push&r, &6pull&r, and &6none&r modes.
ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.desc3=You can upgrade Tubes by clicking them (in tier order) with &6Enriched Alloy&r, &6Reinforced Alloy&r, and &6Atomic Alloy&r. This will upgrade up to 8 connected Cables at once.
ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.desc4=Mechanical Tubes use the MCMultiPart API, which means they can &6share a blockspace with Bits&r.
ftbuniversity.pressurizedtube.task=Any Mechanical Tube

ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.title=Thermo Dynamics
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.subtitle=Make Thermodynamic Conductors
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.desc1=&bThermodynamic Conductors&r can transfer heat energy. Transfer is lossy, with colder biomes losing more heat per block.
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.desc2=Heat... isn't used very often. As such, this quest is completely optional, and does not contribute to the overall completion percentage.
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.desc3=Sneak clicking a connection with a &6Configurator&r allows you to move between &6normal&r, &6push&r, &6pull&r, and &6none&r modes.
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.desc4=You can upgrade Conductors by clicking them (in tier order) with &6Enriched Alloy&r, &6Reinforced Alloy&r, and &6Atomic Alloy&r. This will upgrade up to 8 connected Cables at once.
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.desc5=Thermodynamic Conductors use the MCMultiPart API, which means they can &6share a blockspace with Bits&r.
ftbuniversity.thermoconduct.task=Any Thermodynamic Conductor

ftbuniversity.meklaser.title=Imma Firin Mah Lazor
ftbuniversity.meklaser.subtitle=制作一个 Laser
ftbuniversity.meklaser.desc1=The &bLaser&r uses RF to shoot out a beam from its front end.
ftbuniversity.meklaser.desc2=The Laser beam will damage any mob it touches, lighting them on fire. It will also mine blocks.

ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.title=&lLaser&r
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.subtitle=制作一个 Laser Amplifier
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.desc1=The &bLaser Amplifier&r can accept Laser beams from 5 of its sides, store their energy, then shoot it out the front.
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.desc2=In its GUI, you can set the &6minimum RF required&r to fire, as well as the &6maximum amount it can fire at once&r.
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.desc3=You can also set a &6Delay&r in ticks. The laser will emit for a short pulse, then wait the time set by the delay, then repeat.
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.desc4=The bottom left, you can change the &6Redstone Output&r mode. &6Energy Contents&r will allow a Comparator to output the amount of energy it has, and &6Entity Detection&r will make it emit a signal when the laser is touching an entity.
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.desc5=The bottom right lets you make it only emit the laser beam based on the &6redstone signal it receives&r.
ftbuniversity.laseramplifier.desc6=If the Amplifier is &6not emitting&r the laser, other laser inputs are directly converted to stored RF. You can &6extract&r this with a Universal Cable configured to Pull. Other mods' cables will not work.

ftbuniversity.lasertract.subtitle=制作一个 Laser Tractor Beam
ftbuniversity.lasertract.desc1=The &bLaser Tractor Beam&r accepts Laser Beams from its 5 outer sides, then shoots it out the front.
ftbuniversity.lasertract.desc2=It will &6pick up drops&r from blocks mined and mobs killed.

ftbuniversity.solneut.title=She Turned Me Into a Neut!
ftbuniversity.solneut.subtitle=制作一个 Solar Neutron Activator
ftbuniversity.solneut.desc=The &bSolar Neutron Activator&r uses solar energy to &6convert Lithium gas into Tritium gas&r.

ftbuniversity.mekreactor.title=Disco Reactor
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.subtitle=Construct a Fusion Reactor
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.desc1=The &bFusion Reactor&r is a rather complex multiblock, capable of generating extremely high amounts of RF.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.desc2=To begin with, 制作一个 5x5 star of &bReactor Frames&r (that is, a 3x3 square with another going out the middle of each side).
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.desc3=On the next layer, 制作一个 hollow 5x5 square without corners, again using Reactor Frames.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.desc4=On the third layer, 制作一个 hollow 5x5 square &owith&r corners. 3 of the non-corner blocks must be &bReactor Ports&r, and one must be a &bLaser Focus Matrix&r.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.desc5=The fourth layer should be the same as the second, and the fifth and final layer should be the same as the first, but with a &bReactor Controller&r in the center.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.desc6=Any Frame that isn't on an edge can be replaced with &6Reactor Glass&r.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor.task=74x Reactor Frame

ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.title=Get a Snack, This Quest is All Reading
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.subtitle=Learn how to run the Fusion Reactor
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc1=Seeing as how 5 entire paragraphs were dedicated to &obuilding&r the Fusion Generator, this quest will explain how to &ouse&r it.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc2=The Fusion Reactor is powered by &6Deuterium&r and &6Tritium&r, as well as an unreasonable amount of Laser-power to jumpstart it.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc3=Pump in these two gases via Reactor Ports.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc4=Before being jumpstarted, a &bHohlraum&r full of &6D-T Fuel&r must be inserted into the slot in the Reactor Controller.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc5=In the &6Fuel&r tab of the Reactor Controller, set the &6injection rate&r. This is the combined amount in mB/t of the fuel to be spent. So setting it at 2 would spend 1mB/t of each fuel.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc6=Higher injection rates mean higher temperatures, more RF production, and also more resource cost.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc7=To begin, the Reactor must reach a certain temperature (see &6Statistics&r page in its GUI).
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc8=To reach this temperature, shoot it with a high-powered laser. It's best to do it all at once instead of spreading it out. The Laser Amplifier should have about &6&n600,000,000 RF&r in it before you turn it on, though &6up to 8 million&r may be required.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc9=The resulting reaction, assuming the injection rate is high enough, will &6keep itself hot and running&r.
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc10=At the bottom left, you can see the current amount of RF being generated. &6RF can be extracted from a Reactor Port.&r
ftbuniversity.mekreactor2.desc11=For reference, an injection rate of 50 generates &650,000,000 RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.mekreactorbackup.title=Just in Case
ftbuniversity.mekreactorbackup.subtitle=制作一个 emergency energy backup
ftbuniversity.mekreactorbackup.desc1=As the previous quest stated, it costs upwards of &6600 million RF&r to jumpstart a Reactor. That's a lot of RF.
ftbuniversity.mekreactorbackup.desc2=As such, you should 制作一个 &bemergency energy backup&r that doesn't power anything but the Lasers, &6just in case the Reactor turns itself off without you noticing&r, and your storage gets drained.

ftbuniversity.dtfuel.title=The D in D-T stands for Don't
ftbuniversity.dtfuel.subtitle=Learn about D-T Fuel
ftbuniversity.dtfuel.desc1=&bD-T Fuel&r can also be piped into the Fusion Reactor, but it's a bit more complex.
ftbuniversity.dtfuel.desc2=Normally, you can restrict the amount of Deuterium and Tritium used by changing the injection rate.
ftbuniversity.dtfuel.desc3=However, as D-T Fuel is already mixed and thus doesn't need to be injected, &6it gets used up as fast as possible&r. This is great if you have a huge source of D-T Fuel, but generally that's not the case.

ftbuniversity.meksteam.title=Steam Powered
ftbuniversity.meksteam.subtitle=Water-cool the Reactor
ftbuniversity.meksteam.desc1=With the addition of two more Reactor Ports, you can pipe in Water and pipe out &bSteam&r.
ftbuniversity.meksteam.desc2=Steam can be used in the &rIndustrial Turbine&r, which can generate even more RF in parallel with the Reactor.

ftbuniversity.mekturbine.title=ctf_turbine
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.subtitle=制作一个 Industrial Turbine
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc1=The &bIndustrial Turbine&r is a &oreally&r complex multiblock that uses Steam to generate RF. This quest will explain how to make it.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc2=To begin, 制作一个 &6square platform&r of &bTurbine Casing&r, with the width being an odd number greater/equal to 5.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc3=Make pillars of Turbine Casing in each corner, bringing the &6total max height to twice the width&r (or 18, whichever is lower). Connect the tops of the pillars with more Casing, but leave it hollow.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc4=On top of the center block on the bottom, place a pillar of &bTurbine Rotor&r. Placing more is not necessarily better, as it would leave less room for Steam to flow.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc5=Attach &bTurbine Blades&r to the Rotors. Each Rotor requires 2 Blades. The Blades got longer as more are attached; &6make sure they don't touch the walls&r.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc6=Directly &6on top of the highest Rotor&r, place a &bRotational Complex&r. &6Fill that entire y-level&r with &bPressure Dispersers&r, wall to wall, so that the Rotors are completely separated from the top.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc7=Fill the &6entire layer above&r with &bElectromagnetic Coils&r. These can be &6flush with the Turbine's ceiling&r.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc8=At this point, you are &6done with the Turbine's internals&r. You can finish the walls using either more Turbine Casings, or &bStructural Glass&r.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc9=Place a &bTurbine Vent&r in one of the walls, &6at or above the layer that the Pressure Dispersers are on&r. The more Vents, the higher the flow rate, and thus higher energy production.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc10=Finally, place a &bTurbine Vent&r anywhere in the walls. This is where Steam is input and RF is output.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine.desc11=Once the structure is fully formed, it should emit some Redstone particles.

ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.title=Now That &oThat's&r Out of the Way
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.subtitle=Learn how to run an Industrial Turbine
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.desc1=Now that your Turbine is constructed, you can &blearn how to actually &ouse&r&b the darn thing&r.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.desc2=&6The higher the flow rate, the higher the RF produced&r.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.desc3=The flow rate is based on either the volume of the lower portion of the Turbine or the amount of vents; &6whichever is less&r.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.desc4=In the &6Turbine Statistics&r page of its GUI, you can see what the &6limiting factors&r are. That is, what's stopping it from making more RF/t.
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.desc5=These limiting factors are relative. To produce more RF, increase the amount of whatever is a limiting factor (install more Vents or Blades etc).
ftbuniversity.mekturbine2.desc6=The final RF production is equal to the &6flow multiplied by the Rotor height, multiplied again by 50, then divided by 7&r. All these values are in the Turbine's GUI.

ftbuniversity.mektanks.title=Portable Tanks
ftbuniversity.mektanks.subtitle=制作一个 Fluid Tank
ftbuniversity.mektanks.desc1=&bFluid Tanks&r are single-block fluid containers. Each tier stores more than the last.
ftbuniversity.mektanks.desc2=You can mine a Fluid Tank and it will &6keep its contents&r.
ftbuniversity.mektanks.desc3=They can also be &6used as Buckets&r.
ftbuniversity.mektanks.task=Any Fluid Tank

ftbuniversity.gastank.title=Airtight
ftbuniversity.gastank.subtitle=制作一个 Gas Tank
ftbuniversity.gastank.desc1=&bGas Tanks&r store gas, as the name implies.
ftbuniversity.gastank.desc2=There are &64 tiers&r, each stores more than the last.
ftbuniversity.gastank.task=Gas Tank

ftbuniversity.configurator.title=I Barely Knew 'er!
ftbuniversity.configurator.subtitle=制作一个 Configurator
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc1=The &bConfigurator&r is Mekanism's wrench, using RF to configure blocks.
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc2=Hovering over a Mekanism machine will show the &6color&r of that side (see the quest directly to the left).
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc3=Right-clicking the Configurator on a machine will say in chat its &6current color&r, as well as what it means.
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc4=Sneak right-clicking will &6cycle through all possible colors&r on that face.
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc5=There is also special interactions when clicked on pipes:
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc6=Right-clicking the center of a pipe will toggle its &6redstone sensitivity&r.
ftbuniversity.configurator.desc7=Sneak right-clicking a connection will toggle it between &6neutral&r, &6push&r, &6pull&r, and &6none&r.

ftbuniversity.mekcolors.title=Colors of the Wind
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.subtitle=Learn about Mekanism's olor modes
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc1=The Configurator color codes the input/output of each side of a machine, when held. These colors are:
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc2=&7Grey&r: no input or output.
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc3=&4Dark Red&r: input for items and gasses.
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc4=&1Dark Blue&r: output for items and gasses.
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc5=&aGreen&r: RF input
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc6=&dPurple&r: input for secondary material for the Metallurgic Infuser
ftbuniversity.mekcolors.desc7=&eYellow&r: neutral for fluids, must be pushed/pulled in the pipe

ftbuniversity.mekbin.title=Bins
ftbuniversity.mekbin.subtitle=制作一个 Bin
ftbuniversity.mekbin.desc1=&bBins&r can store a large amount of a single item, sort of like a Drawer.
ftbuniversity.mekbin.desc2=Actually, exactly like a Drawer. Right-click to insert, punch to extract, the whole shebang.
ftbuniversity.mekbin.desc3=However, if you put one by itself in a crafting grid, you can pull its items out.
ftbuniversity.mekbin.task=Any Bin

ftbuniversity.dynamictank.title=RIP Xycraft
ftbuniversity.dynamictank.subtitle=制作一个 Dynamic Tank
ftbuniversity.dynamictank.desc1=&bDynamic Tanks&r are freeform multiblock fluid containers.
ftbuniversity.dynamictank.desc2=制作一个y hollow cuboid (that is, the whole thing must have only 6 sides) out of Dynamic Tank blocks.
ftbuniversity.dynamictank.desc3=You can replace any non-corner with &bStructural Glass&r to be able to see how much fluid is inside.
ftbuniversity.dynamictank.desc4=Place &bDynamic Valves&r in any surface, aside from the edges, to automatically input and extract fluids.
ftbuniversity.dynamictank.desc5=Every block in its volume (including the walls) gives it &616 buckets&r of fluid it can store.

